title: mother's cinnamon rolls
directions: Add yeast to lukewarm milk; let stand until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and shortening; mix well.
Add 2 whole eggs and beat again.
Add flour (1 cup at a time), beating after each addition.

title: praline strips
directions: Put crackers in an ungreased tin pan.
Heat margarine and sugar to boiling.
Cut down heat to low for 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon and spread over crackers.
Cut in strips while warm.

title: barbecued spicy chicken
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except chicken.
Simmer, covered, about 1/2 hour; stir occasionally.
Season chicken with salt and pepper. Place, bone side down, over medium-hot coals.
Grill 25 minutes. Turn skin side down; grill 20 minutes more.
Brush barbecue sauce over chicken.
Continue grilling until tender, 10 to 15 minutes, turning frequently and basting with sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onions, green
peppers and salt in large bowl or earthenware crock. Cover vegetables with small ice cubes and cover with a weighted plate and set aside for about 3 hours.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a paper bag.
Drop in beef and shake well.
Mix with oil in a casserole baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes (stir once).
Add vegetables, etc., water and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Cover.
Bake at 350° approximately 2 hours.

title: western baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add beans, mustard and catsup.
Mix well.
Cover and cook until bubbly and hot, about 20 minutes. Very quick and easy.
Freezes well.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Brown hamburger meat and diced onion in olive oil.
Drain excess oil.
Add cut up tomatoes, tomato paste and water (may need more or less water).
Then add sugar, salt, basil leaves and garlic.
Let sauce come to a boil; turn down on low to simmer and add meatballs.

title: bacon and eggs spaghetti
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cook spaghetti as label directs; drain.
Meanwhile, in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp.
With slotted spoon, remove to paper towels; set aside.

title: 15 minute pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cucumbers; simmer for 10 minutes. Add cucumbers and boil for only 5 minutes.
Pack in jars, cover with syrup and seal.
Yield: One gallon.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil first four ingredients to hard boil stage.
Pour peanuts in, also butter.
Cook until golden brown, stirring constantly. Take off stove and add soda; mix.
Pour immediately into 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Spread as thin as possible.

title: mash potato casserole
directions: Prepare mash potatoes per instructions on box for 6 to 8 servings.
Mix corn and peas or any combination of vegetables you like into potatoes.
Add cheese and ham.
Mix well.
Put into flat well-greased baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let stand 30 minutes.
Bake in casserole dish for 1 hour at 350° until hot.
Turn down to 250° and cook until done.
Should be moist.
Dip servings with spoon.

title: moist and easy banana cake
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 40 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: "fruit whip"
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve in attractive bowl.

title: miniature holiday cheesecakes
directions: Place wafers flat side down on bottom of each of 18 foil or paper-lined baking cups.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs together.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: applesauce filling
directions: Combine and cook until thick; cool.
Spread on cake.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Place carrots, onion, potatoes and cloves in large pot.
Cover with water and bring to a boil (with bay leaf).
Simmer 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Puree the mixture.
Return to pot and add milk.
Bring to boil again.
Remove from heat and season. Stir in well beaten yolks and butter.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, onions and cashews.
Spread on ham slices. Roll up and slice into 3/4-inch pieces.
Secure with toothpick and place on serving tray.
Refrigerate, covered, until serving time.

title: barley bean soup
directions: Soak dried lima beans for a few hours or overnight.
Drain and add 2 quarts of water in a heavy saucepan.
Add neck bones, onion, parsley, dill weed, barley, salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil and then turn the heat low and simmer for 2 hours or until beans and meat are tender.
Remove bones and cut up chunks of meat.
Return meat to the soup.
Remove bay leaves.
Chill and remove solidified fat.
Reheat when ready to serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: smokey bean skillet
directions: In skillet, combine onion, green pepper and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and simmer about 5 minutes more, if necessary, to reduce liquid.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Mix in milk and flour, then coconut.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: cheese sauce dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in the container of a blender.
Blend on low speed until creamy, adding more milk if necessary to produce the desired consistency.
Keep this sauce refrigerated.
Use it as a dressing or an accompaniment to poultry and fish.
It can be substituted for sour cream in a number of dips, spreads and dressings, but cannot be substituted for sour cream in heated food such as stroganoff.
Contains 44 calories per serving, 1 gram of fat.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/2 cup sugar and oil.
Add eggs separately and sour cream.
Combine all of these ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour over batter in pan.
Pour remaining cake batter in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and 1/2 cup pecans.
Pour over cake while still warm.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: In a deep large skillet, saute the meat and onions over medium-high heat until meat is cooked through and onions are softened. Add tomatoes, their juice, cinnamon, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup Parmesan. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, and simmer the sauce for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, salt, 1/4 cup sugar, egg and 1 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer. Add remaining flour and blend.
Use enough flour to knead for a soft dough.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Roll on board 12 x 9-inches.
Spread with soft butter.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Roll up and cut into 15 pieces. Place cut side down in pan.
Let rise until light; bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Stir in flour; add water and cook until thickened.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir to melt.
Add broccoli and eggs; stir, but do not cook.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch casserole dish; top with bread crumbs and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eat more casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
Meanwhile cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain macaroni and combine it with hamburger.
Add onion, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic powder, Accent and taco seasoning.
Last fold in corn and beans.
Put mixture in a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole in 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Great with a salad and hot rolls.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute until onions are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, green chilies, sugar, cumin, salt, oregano and basil. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: ham and cheese bites
directions: Blend cream cheese, Blue cheese and deviled ham.
Chill. Shape into balls.
Roll in parsley and chill until serving.
Use pretzel sticks as picks.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; add eggs, vinegar, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes.
It will thicken as it cools.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Fry sliced Vidalia onions in butter until tender.
Put in pie shell.
Beat eggs; mix in milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken and mushroom gravy
directions: Brown chicken in Dutch oven.
Add soup and onions.
Add thyme and wine.
Cook on low until tender, usually 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add water if necessary.
Serve with rice.

title: irish crunchy brown bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and grease a 1 pound loaf pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour into large well buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Boil in water until tender, then drain.
Cook beef in skillet with oil (if needed).
Add onions and bell pepper.
Cook, stirring, until nicely browned.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and oregano.
Blend, then add tomato sauce. Arrange slices of eggplant in baking dish alternately with meat sauce and cheese.
Repeat in layers with cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy mex casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in other ingredients. Crumble as many chips as desired.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple fudge
directions: Put all ingredients together in heavy saucepan.
Cook, stirring often until soft ball forms in cold water.
Pour into buttered platter.
Cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cake and topping
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add oatmeal-water mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add, beating well.
Bake in well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cook and stir cornmeal and water until mixture becomes stiff and begins to form a ball (about 6 minutes).
Remove from heat; add milk, 1 tablespoon oil and onion.
Stir until smooth. Gradually stir into beaten eggs.
Stir dry ingredients together. Add to cornmeal mixture and blend thoroughly.
Heat fat (about 1-inch deep) to 375°.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot fat. Fry 6 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Makes 24 to 30.

title: pancho's cheese dip
directions: Bring all ingredients, except cheese, to a boil over medium heat.
Then simmer low for 10 minutes.
Cut cheese in small squares and put in blender.
Pour hot mixture on top, then blend.

title: shrimp-n-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Cut shrimp and eggs into small pieces.
Combine macaroni, shrimp and eggs with remaining ingredients; sprinkle celery seed on top.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer refried beans in deep dish, 13 x 9-inch, or 2 small dishes.
Chop in jalapeno peppers.
Layer avocado.
Mix together sour cream with mayo and taco seasoning mix and layer.
Layer onions, tomatoes, cheese and olives.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 50 minutes, or until knife edge inserted halfway between center and outside edge comes out clean.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; blend on high. Pour into 9 inch greased pie dish. Bake at 350° for 50 - 55 minutes. Do not pour into a pie shell, this is a crustless pie.

title: my slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add about 1/3 bottle Italian dressing and stir.
The longer it sits in refrigerator, better it is.

title: pork chops ole
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops in oil.
Salt and pepper. Meanwhile, combine rice, water, sauce and taco seasoning; mix well. Arrange chops over rice.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover; top with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts. Yield:
6 servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, pumpkin, and margarine. Mix baking powder, soda, and cinnamon to flour. Add this to sugar mixture. Stir in nuts. Bake at 350° in a deep large cookie sheet until done. Cool. Top with frosting.

title: orange dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening, hot water, eggs, salt and 1 cup flour.
Stir in yeast and add remaining flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn dough onto flour; roll 1/4-inch thick and spread with Orange Filling.
Roll up and slice 1 1/2 inches thick.
Put in buttered muffin pans and rise 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all together and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Fry meat and onion; drain.
Boil until tender the cabbage; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and cook/simmer until tender and spices are mixed.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple and water in pan.
Add sugar and lemon juice. Soak gelatin in cold water.
Combine heated pineapple mix with gelatin mixture.
Set in refrigerator until jelled.
Beat in mayonnaise and cottage cheese.
Pour into mold and set in refrigerator.
Serves 12 to 16.
I leave out the sugar and lemon for diabetics.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions on box.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Layer vanilla wafers, then bananas, then pudding.
Continue until mixture is used.

title: crab supreme
directions: Beat ingredients together, then add two envelopes of Knox unflavored gelatine, dissolved in 4 teaspoons boiling water.
Let chill.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl as given.
Do not beat until last item is added.
Beat well.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes in a Bundt or tube pan only.

title: pulled mints
directions: Cook
in heavy aluminum pot the sugar, butter and water to 275°
on candy thermometer.
Pour on buttered marbled slab to cool.
When cool enough to handle, pick up and pull.
After pulling
a	little, add flavoring and color.
Continue to pull until candy
gets harder to pull and has a dry look.
Pull out in long rope and cut with shears.
Do not stir
while cooking.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: In order given, mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 12 minutes.

title: mushroom-stuffed pork chops
directions: Have butcher
cut
pocket in each chop.
Saute onion in butter until transparent;	add mushrooms, few leaves of thyme, parsley and crumbs.
Mix well and remove from heat.
Season to taste; stir in beaten egg.
Stuff chops.
Brown in pan.
Bake in a greased casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: ham and cheese lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles in boiling salted water just until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
In medium saucepan, cook onion and green peppers in margarine until tender; blend in flour.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in Swiss cheese until melted.
Stir in ham and mushrooms.
Arrange half the noodles in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the ham mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serve 6.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake cups with vanilla wafers and fill 3/4 full of filling.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Top with cherry pie filling or strawberries or chocolate shavings, etc.
Delicious!

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Spread onto flour tortillas.
Roll up and cut into bite-size pieces.
Chill and serve with salsa.

title: pecan brittle(an old favorite)
directions: Sprinkle nuts
over buttered shallow pan.
Put sugar in heavy iron
pan
and
melt
very
slowly, stirring constantly. When syrup is
a golden color, remove quickly and add salt and soda. Pour thin layer over nuts.
Break in pieces when cool.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Tear apart from bones.
Put in baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch) with 1 cup of cream of celery soup and 1 can of cream of chicken soup.
Mix Stove Top dressing as directed and add on top with 1 cup of chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good and easy.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, sweet milk, flour, cocoa and vanilla in boiler.
Cook until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell. Top with the 4 egg whites which have been beaten with sugar, then brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water and mix.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves together and mix into the creamed shortening mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in olive oil.
Saute onions, peppers and celery.
Mix V-8 juice, tomato paste and spices in 4 quart saucepan and preheat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Blend ground beef, onions, peppers and celery in sauce.
Simmer on low heat for at least 4 hours.
If it becomes too thick, add 1 cup cooking sherry. Never use water.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Combine fruit with 1 cup flour and baking powder.
In another bowl, cream butter with sugars.
Add eggs, flour and lemon extract.
Add fruit and flour mixture with chopped pecans.
Fill a greased and floured tube pan 3/4 full.
Bake 2 hours at 300°. Loaf pans may be used.

title: cherry squares
directions: Add sugar and butter in a large bowl.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and extract.
Pour batter into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Mark the batter very lightly into squares.
Put 1 tablespoon filling into each square.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie(mock pecan)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Boil for 7 minutes.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Drain and cool.
Add onion and bell pepper. Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over vegetables and cover. Marinate for 12 hours or more.
Drain before serving.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: aunt fan's cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; beat until creamy.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add cereal, nuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Drop on very lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crab meat cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except nuts.
Roll into a ball. Roll ball in nuts.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and egg.
Then mix in persimmon pulp. Add dry ingredients and then nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet and press a walnut half on top to flatten a little.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: "snicker" yogurt pie
directions: Mix softened Cool Whip, pudding mix and peanut butter together until well blended.
Add to the softened vanilla yogurt.
Pour into pans sprayed with Pam and freeze.
Makes several pies.

title: doug's famous jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet or heavy pan, cook or saute kielbasa until brown.
Drain; put aside.
Cook chicken until tender.
Saute onion and garlic.
Put everything in a large frying pan or saucepan and cook until nice and brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter 10 minutes.
Spread over graham crackers.
Add bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip, pecans, chocolate syrup and cherries.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Everything except boiling coffee can be mixed together at once.
Stir and slowly add coffee.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple salad(yields 12 servings)
directions: Drain juice off pineapple into measuring cup.
Add enough water to make one cup of liquid.
Now pour the cup of liquid into a saucepan and set aside.
Mix sugar, arrowroot and eggs together. Now add sugar mixture to liquid.
Stir together.
Now cook this mixture to pudding stage (stir frequently).
When mixture is cooked, set off burner and let come to room temperature.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat 1/3 cup sugar into egg yolks.
Add salt.
Stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture coats spoon.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar, beating until it forms soft peaks.
Add to custard and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and rum flavoring.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Pour into punch bowl or cups.
Dot with islands of whipped cream and dash with nutmeg.

title: baked asparagus or spinach*
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place asparagus or wilted spinach in a baking dish.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Top with chopped butter, chopped garlic and sprinkle with chopped Italian parsley.
Cover and bake for 5 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more. This feeds about 4. Can easily be doubled and fits nicely in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish for entertaining.

title: bisquick gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, milk, molasses and shortening.
Blend with dry ingredients.
Bake in oiled 7-inch square pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: In heavy skillet, lightly brown meats, onions and garlic in oil (drain fat).
Add tomatoes, paste, water and all the seasonings; simmer, uncovered for about 25 minutes, stirring often.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Drain peaches and arrange with cherries in sugar mixture. Mix cake as directed; spread over fruit.
Bake at 350° until done (45 to 50 minutes).
Let stand five minutes.
Turn upside-down onto large platter.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions, but add 2 tablespoons creme de menthe; bake as directed.
Pour fudge sauce over cooled cake; mix 2 tablespoons creme de menthe into Cool Whip and spread on cake.
Refrigerate.

title: jungle juice
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Boil and cool.
Add Kool-Aid.
Blend bananas and strawberries in blender.
Add to Kool-Aid mixture. Add all juices.
Put in containers and freeze.
At time of serving, add room temperature Sprite.
Makes 4 (2-gallon) punch bowls.

title: corn, tomato and rice casserole
directions: Cook onions and bell peppers in margarine.
Add to other ingredients; thicken with flour.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with cheese and let it melt.
Serves 15 to 20.
Great for church covered dish dinners! Recipe may be easily halved.

title: beef tips
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in crock-pot on low for 6 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and place in shallow baking pan.
Season as desired.
Spread soup evenly over beans.
Top with whole slices of cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Top with onion rings.
Brown and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Sift cocoa, baking powder and salt together and add to mixture.
Add milk and flour alternately. Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a big bowl, mix the pumpkin, oil, eggs, water and sugar. Sift the rest of the ingredients together over wax paper.
Add these slowly to the pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 (5 x 9-inch) loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab dip
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup of crab meat.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except the cocktail sauce (save this for the top spread).
You really need to use your hands to mix this well. Spread mixture on a flat dish.
Top with the cocktail sauce. Sprinkle the set aside crab meat on top.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Save out 1/2 c. flour; mix soda in buttermilk. Add 2 1/2 c. flour and buttermilk to sugar mixture. Mix cocoa in boiling water and add to batter. Dice apple in small pieces and roll in the 1/2 c. flour; add to batter. Add vanilla and stir. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes two 9 Inch layers.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Slice English muffins in half, then quarter each half and arrange on 2 cookie sheets.
Mix together the crab meat, butter, Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, seasoned salt and garlic salt.
Spread the mixture on the muffins and freeze them for 30 minutes or longer.
Remove from freezer and place in oven.
Broil until they puff up and are slightly golden brown.
(Starts to bubble.)

title: apricot seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot apricot juice.
Add softened cream cheese and milk. Beat until smooth.
Add mashed apricots.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Serves 10-12.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Tear dried beef and place in bottom of roaster or cake pan. Place chicken breasts on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Remove cover and bake another 1/2 hour.
Serve hot with wild rice, regular rice or noodles.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding; beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture. Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put into a suitable size casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: slovenske palacinky(slovak pancakes)
directions: Beat the eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and one cup milk.
Beat very well and then add flour gradually, putting in remaining milk. Beat until very smooth.
Have greased skillet hot.
Put about two tablespoons of the mixture on this skillet.
Brown on both sides. A filling may be used such as jelly or jam, etc.
This recipe will make about 30 palacinky.

title: cottage cheese apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and congeal.

title: rich chocolate pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir about 1/2 cup milk mixture into egg yolks.
Stir egg yolk mixture back into saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute (and no longer), stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon into dessert bowls.
Refrigerate, covered, with plastic wrap, until chilled, 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: red cabbage and onions
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, vinegar and salt; let stand 5 minutes. Heat butter in a large skillet. Add cabbage, turning 2 times or more. Stir in rest of ingredients. Cook, covered, on low heat for 1 hour.

title: purple passion salad
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well with other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon, sunflower seeds, raisins and red onion in a large bowl.

title: spice tea
directions: Put in container and use as needed.
Mix 1 to 2 teaspoons in very hot water and drink.

title: aunt irene's warm punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large crock-pot.
Simmer over low heat for at least one hour.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind frozen blueberries in blender at high speed.
Combine sugar and marshmallows with blueberries.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add remaining ingredients, folding in whipped cream. Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cornish hens in orange sauce
directions: Cook rice as directed on box and drain.
Combine rice and the following:
onion, 1/2 teaspoon celery salt and parsley.
Then add butter, eggs, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and stuff hens with rice mixture.
Place extra rice on bottom of large, deep baking pan.
Arrange hens on top of rice and coat hens generously with whipped margarine.
Sprinkle lightly with additional salt, minced garlic, minced onion and parsley flakes. Bake 1 hour in 375° oven.
Keep hens moist by basting with prepared Orange Sauce.

title: grandpa george's spicy shrimp
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Add spices and shrimp.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Serve as appetizer with French bread and butter.

title: easy day chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Drain corn and peas.
Add to crock-pot.
Peel potatoes and cut in cubes.
Add to chicken and vegetables.
Pour tomato sauce over chicken, potatoes and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low setting 4 to 6 hours.
Can also be baked at 350° for an hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat.
Put in casserole dish.
Layer all, first meat, beans, corn and tomato soup.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: white texas cake
directions: Beat Crisco, sugar and egg whites until fluffy.
Add soda, salt and flour.
Mix buttermilk, vanilla and almond extract in with other mixture.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook broccoli and bouillon in water.
Do not drain.
In blender, put milk, cheese cubes and flour.
Cover and process at grind.
Add mixture to broccoli.
Add half and half.
Cook, stirring frequently, over medium heat until hot and mixture thickens.

title: e-z lasagna
directions: *Make the night before or at least 2 hours before it will be baked.

title: old time beef stew
directions: In dutch oven, brown meat in 2 Tbsp. oil., turning often. Add 2 cups hot water and next 9 ingredients. Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf and garlic. Add vegetables. Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes more. Mix 1 cup milk and 2 Tbsp. flour together and add to stew slowly, stirring. Cook and stir until bubbly. Stir 3 minutes. Serves 4.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 55 minutes, divided.

title: stir-fry with soy sauce
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, garlic and 1/2 cup water.
Set aside.
In a large skillet stir-fry meat and vegetables 4 minutes.
Add soy sauce mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat flour mix.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chocolate chips and nuts on top before baking.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes a moist cake.

title: strawberries and cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare one pie crust according to package directions.
Use a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.
Cool.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Blend milk, flour, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir in rest of the ingredients and pour into a 9 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Cook last 5 ingredients until thick and pour over fruit; mix.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar; mix.
Add cold water; boil for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add pineapple, lemon and orange juice.
To serve, add 4 quarts ice water and ginger ale.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of bacon drippings.
Crumble bacon and mix with onions, squash, bread crumbs, milk and seasonings. Add cheese, saving a bit to sprinkle on top.
Place in casserole dish and bake in medium oven for about 1 hour.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in freezer can.
Pack ice and salt around can.
Freeze by hand or electric mixer.
This is very good!

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Stir together.
Bake in miniature muffin pan that has been greased for 12 to 14 minutes at 425°.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Bring peppers, sugar and vinegar to a boil, then add Certo and bring to a boil again.
Pour into jars.

title: sheila's chicken stuff
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook covered at 250° to 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: soft sour milk cookie
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter; add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add alternately with milk with vinegar in it.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until set but not brown.

title: tuna quickie
directions: Mix soup and
milk.
Add rice, tuna, onion, pimento and Tabasco sauce.
Mix
well
and
pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for
minutes
or
until bubbly.
The last few minutes of cooking time, sprinkle cheese over top of casserole and let melt.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, flour and cocoa.
Combine milk, egg yolks, melted margarine or butter.
Beat with wire whisk. Gradually add milk mixture to sugar mixture.
Stir until smooth. Cook chocolate mixture over medium heat until thick and bubbly (10 minutes).
Make meringue with remaining sugar, egg whites and cream of tartar.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Line salad plates with greens.
Arrange grapefruit and kiwi fruit on greens.
Top with grapes.
Drizzle each serving with a tablespoon of French dressing.

title: picadillo
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil with garlic. Add beef and brown. Drain fat. Add tomato sauce, water, raisins and olives. Simmer on medium-low heat about 50 minutes until fluid cooks down. Stir occasionally. Serve over white rice.

title: jack-o-lantern cookies
directions: Onto waxed paper, sift together flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in molasses and pumpkin. Blend in flour mixture.
Divide the dough into 4 equal parts; refrigerate, wrapped in wax paper, at least 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and dry soup mix.
Arrange chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with cooked rice, spooning sauce on rice.

title: velvet peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, canned milk and regular milk and boil to a soft ball stage.
Add
remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan and cool.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line an 8-inch square pan with foil, letting sides extend.
Lightly grease foil.
Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Stir until blended.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla with a whisk.
Stir in flour, then nuts.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 22 to 27 minuets or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and lift foil out by the ends.

title: baked sweet potato chips
directions: Peel and cut sweet potatoes into thin slices; line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Place sliced sweet potatoes in one layer on the cookie sheet.
Spray with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 20 minutes.
A good substitute for potato chips.

title: tiny cream puffs
directions: Melt margarine in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once and stir vigorously.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition until mixture is smooth.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon about 1 1/2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes. Remove with spatula and cool on rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add chicken; cook and stir until thick.
Stir in cream, salt and dash of pepper.
Put broccoli in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of sauce on broccoli.
Place chicken over this.
To remaining sauce, add cheese and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle extra cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot (if just made, about 20 minutes; if cold, about 35 to 40 minutes).
Recipe reheats well in microwave.

title: hearty beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Parboil potatoes and
carrots
in
salted water 20 minutes. Drain.
Combine
soup, milk and catsup.
Brown meat and onion. Drain.
In
2 1/2 quart casserole, alternate layers of vegetables, soup mixture
and
meat, ending with soup mixture. Saute mushrooms in butter
or margarine.
Place on top of soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yield:
six servings.

title: perfection salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple juice and water.
Pour over jello.
Stir until dissolved. Add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Cool until it begins to set.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in bowl of jello mix.
Stir thoroughly and put in refrigerator. Pineapple chunks may be added, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together (except corn flakes) and put in greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes and bake at 325° until bubbles and brown on top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup strawberry juice.
Add bananas, one at a time.
(Stir in juice.)
Add pineapple and stir.
In 9 x 13-inch dish, pour 1/2 mixture in bottom of dish.
Let set up good.
Take sour cream and spread over top of salad; add remaining mixture.
Cover and let it set.

title: rainbow float
directions: Fill glass halfway to the top with fruit drink.
Then put in sherbet.
Fill the glass with soda.
Serve right away.

title: best ever biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, cream of tartar and salt together; mix well.
Cut shortening until its cut up fine in flour mixture.
Add milk; stir until all mixed.
Pour out on a floured table; knead dough 10 to 12 strokes, then roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out biscuits; put in a greased pan.
Pout oil, milk or butter on top of biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour melted margarine into mixing bowl.
Put a layer of crushed corn flakes in baking dish.
Spread 5 cups of shredded cabbage on top of corn flakes.

title: congealed salad for diabetics
directions: Dissolve jello and hot water.
Slice bananas and mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 into a dish.
Spread sour cream over the jello when it has set up.
Spread the remainder of mixture over all this and refrigerate.

title: apricot balls
directions: Peel oranges being careful to remove white membrane. Grind apricots and orange peel in food processor.
Place in saucepan and add juice from oranges.
Add sugar.
Cook together for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Pour into platter and let cool. Form into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Makes 8 dozen (1-inch balls).

title: pepper steak
directions: Lightly brown chopped onion and garlic in oil.
Add steak and soy sauce.
Brown steak, then cover and simmer until steak is nearly done.
Add peppers and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until peppers are cooked to desired stage.
Make a paste of cornstarch and water to thicken the broth, if desired. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: layered chef's salad
directions: Layer each item as listed 2 to 3 times in bowl to fill bowl. Top with remaining sliced, boiled eggs and/or bacon and onions for garnish.
Chill well.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Add milk and stir well.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Beat egg yolks lightly.
Add a small amount of hot mixture and mix well.
Add to remaining hot mixture.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, coconut and margarine.
Mix well.
Top with meringue; brown under broiler.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with fluff until smooth. Refrigerate until ready to use.
For "Adults Only" parties you can spike the dip with your favorite liqueur.
Very easy!
Very tasty!

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Set aside.
Combine soup, milk, onion, peppers and black pepper.
Place over low heat; add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Mix macaroni and tuna; blend in cheese sauce.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 325° oven about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.
The sauce may be heated in a microwave if desired until cheese is melted.

title: moonshine
directions: Beat egg whites into a very stiff froth, then gradually add powdered sugar, beating for not less than 15 minutes.
Cut peach preserves into tiny pieces; fold into mixture.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Boil beans for 45 minutes in water and salt.
Pour beans in a slow cooker; add remaining ingredients.
Cook well (1 to 1 1/2 hours to all day).
Serve on hot cooked rice.

title: forever ambers
directions: Mix all together good.
Cook in oven 30 minutes on a well-greased pan at 275° to 300°.
Take out with teaspoon.
Spoon onto powdered sugar.
Roll in balls.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell and cool. Slice fresh strawberries in crust. Mix sugar, water and cornstarch and cook until clear. Take off heat and add Jell-O. Let cool. Pour over berries in pie shell. Refrigerate and garnish with Cool Whip when serving.

title: red chicken chilaquiles stew
directions: Bring the chicken stock to a boil in a deep skillet.
Sprinkle the chicken breasts with salt and pepper and add to broth.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, or until cooked through.
Lift out the chicken, reserving the stock, wrap in a damp towel and set aside to cool.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a stockpot over medium heat. Saute the onions with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoons pepper until soft.
Add the garlic and cook 2 minutes, until aroma is released.
Add the tomatoes and salsa and bring to a boil.
Add the reserved chicken stock and simmer 10 minutes.
When the chicken is cool enough to handle, shred it into strips.

title: chicken divan crepes
directions: Over medium heat, melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce; cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add 2 cups cheese.
Empty sour cream into medium bowl; gradually add hot cheese sauce, stirring constantly.

title: georgia's best cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or just until edges turn brown.

title: strawberry chews
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using 1 package of jello and form into berries.
Roll in the remaining 1/2 package of jello. With a toothpick, apply green confectioners sugar frosting on stem end to form some leaves.

title: pasta with mushrooms marsala
directions: Slice mushrooms.
Slice garlic cloves thin.
Saute mushrooms and garlic in olive oil until liquid has evaporated and garlic pieces are brown, but not burned.
Add Marsala.
Boil briefly and then remove from heat.
Sprinkle chopped parsley over mixture. Boil pasta al dente.
Top with mushroom sauce.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash pats
directions: Cook squash according to package directions; drain well.
Mash squash.
Combine squash and egg; stir well.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Add squash mixture and onion; stir until blended.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in all other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground chuck, bacon and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain fat from pan.
In a casserole dish, place meat mixture.
Add catsup, sugar, mustard, vinegar, baked beans, kidney beans and drained butter beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: 20 minute tuna and rice dinner
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until tender (not brown).
Stir in vegetables, milk and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in tuna, Minute rice and parsley.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Blend flour; pour in milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes.
Put crabmeat in bowl suitable for mixing and pour cooked sauce over crabmeat.
Blend well; transfer to lightly greased casserole and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mrs. c. apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add the others.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: mom's old-time buttermilk gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and molasses.
Mix well. Mix and sift flour, spices and salt.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour mixture to molasses mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: lemon cornmeal pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Chill cookies; crush in blender until consistency of potting soil.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add a few Oreo crumbs to mixture.
In an 8-inch flower pot or plastic cups, layer pudding and crumbs.
Make sure top layer is Oreo crumbs.
Decorate as desired.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix like pie dough.
Put into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together sugars, eggs, salad oil and vanilla.
Mix both together and add rest of ingredients.
Chill dough.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
For crisp cookie, bake longer and chewy cookie, bake shorter.

title: french fried chicken
directions: Season chicken. Dip in eggs, then roll in fish fry.
Preheat skillet of oil to 375°.
Place chicken in skillet and cover.
Turn chicken often so as to brown evenly.
Uncover skillet to allow it to become crispy, 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: kitchree
directions: Soak lentils for 1/2 hour.
Fry mustard seed in some oil until they jump.
Add cumin, chili, garlic, ginger, onion and cinnamon stick; cook for a few minutes.
Add turmeric and cauliflower. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add drained lentils and some butter; stir and add rice and water.
Simmer, covered, until cooked. Additional water may need to be added.
When almost done, add salt and cook a little longer.
May add a tablespoon of lemon juice and some green coriander and sweetened coconut at the end.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, mixed with flour, salt, margarine and vanilla.
In unbaked crust, place pecan pieces and pour over other mixture.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 225°.

title: onion pickles
directions: Peel onions; slice and sprinkle with salt.
Cover with ice and let stand for 3 hours; drain well.
Put in medium pot and mix with all other ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over onions and heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Place in jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pizza
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Press evenly over bottom of 12-inch round baking pan, forming a ring around the edge.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows and chocolate chips over top.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes longer or until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Cool and cut into wedges.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add fruit.
Pour half the jello mixture into a glass bowl.
Let it set.
Top with the sour cream mixed with Cool Whip.
(I use light sour cream and lite Cool Whip.)
Pour the rest of the jello on top.
Chill until set.

title: special cole slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and seeds.
Bring to a boil; pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Store in airtight containers. Keeps for many weeks in refrigerator.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour graham cracker crumbs over melted margarine.
Sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips and walnuts in order given over margarine and graham cracker mixture.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top begins to lightly brown.
Allow to cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Put marshmallows (cut up) in a double boiler and heat until all are melted; then cool.
Add grapefruit pieces to this mixture, stirring continually.
Place all in pie shell and put Cool Whip on top, then add nuts.

title: four layer delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine flour, butter, and pecans and press into a 9 x 13 in. pan.
Bake 15 min.
Let cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Prepare strawberry gelatin according to directions on the box. Preheat oven to 375° and bake pie crust until golden brown.
Slice fresh strawberries.
When pie crust is brown, set aside to cool. After pie crust cools and the gelatin begins to set.
Pour the gelatin into the pie crust.
Spread the fresh strawberries into pie crust.
Stir into gelatin.
Add a thick layer of whipped cream and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together with mixer on medium speed.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry winks cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and cherries.
Roll 1 teaspoon of dough in corn flakes.
Top with cherry.
Bake at 375° on greased cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Brown hamburger; add onions.
Cook until well done.
Drain fat.
Add beans and heat through.

title: watergate salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and stir until well blended.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, place on lettuce leaves.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine morsels and condensed milk in heavy saucepan. Warm over lowest possible heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly in foil lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Lift from pan; remove foil.

title: homemade blue cheese dressing
directions: Mash cream cheese and Blue cheese together.
Blend in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add salt, pepper and celery salt to taste. Thin with milk, if needed.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Remove from heat; stir in flour.
Return to heat.
Add milk; stir until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add peas, well drained, the red salmon and the juice of the salmon. Put it all in a large casserole dish.
Make the drop biscuits. Put on lightly floured board and place on top of casserole, pie crust fashion.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until top is brown.
Serve with salad.

title: bean-corn casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients, except last two.
Salt and pepper the contents of dish, then combine crackers (crushed) and melted oleo.
Place cracker mix over casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Stir cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in cooked shrimp, cocktail sauce and onions.
Shape into a log and garnish with parsley.
Chill thoroughly.

title: chicken and artichokes
directions: Break and fry chicken; put aside.
In same oil, cook onion until golden; add mushrooms and then add artichoke hearts, (cut in half and then in fourths or thirds).
Cook a short time about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add chicken broth and 1/2 can water or wine.
Simmer; add cornstarch.
Last add chicken; cook a little longer.
Enjoy.

title: moist and fruity rainbow cake
directions: Place cake layers top side up in clean 9-inch pans.
Prick with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add cold water and pour 1/2 over each cake layer. Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip pans in warm water for 10 seconds, then turn onto plate.
Frost with Cool Whip and chill.
Store in refrigerator.

title: white sauce(like at hamblins)
directions: Mix well and keep in refrigerator.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Put a layer of cooked noodles in casserole dish, a layer of tuna fish, a layer of cream of mushroom soup, with the milk added. Repeat until casserole is filled.
Sprinkle top with cracker meal.
Cook in moderate oven until thoroughly hot and browned on top.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat.
Mix dry ingredients and add along with raw apples, vanilla and raisins.
Add nuts. Bake for 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: creamy dijon chicken(yield: 6-8 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in cookie sheet with rolled edges.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-fat and easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken breasts in a large skillet or electric skillet.
Mix well and place chicken breasts on top.
Spoon sauce over breasts.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 4.

title: lye soap
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set up.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Mix soda with cake flour.
Add to creamed mixture, buttermilk, alternating with flour & soda.
Beat in coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 - 8-inch cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 min.
Let layers cool in pan for 10 min. then turn out onto racks to cool.
Great!

title: quick tapioca pudding
directions: Soak the first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Bring to a boil. Stir in the vanilla.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Cool; do not stir for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Bake in a tube pan (greased and floured) for 1 1/2 hours at 275°. Let cool completely before removing from pan.

title: chocolate peek-a-boos
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Put milk into sauce pan and add butter, heat to boiling point.
Add dry ingredients all at once to hot liquid, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture leaves sides of pan in smooth compact ball, stirring vigorously. Remove from heat.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating smooth again.
Add vanilla, mix well. Drop by half tsp. 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place 2-3 chips on each cookie.
Cover with a tsp. of dough. Bake at 375 for 15-20 minutes.
Sprinkle with confection sugar if desired.
Cool.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-cook banana pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir until thick.
Then layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: pizza crust
directions: Soak yeast in 3/4 cup warm water for 5 minutes.
Combine rest of ingredients into large bowl.
Add yeast.
Cover and let raise 10 minutes.
Oil 2 cookie sheets or jelly roll pans.
Oil your hands and divide dough in 2.
Using your hands, press dough in pans.
Smaller pans will give a thicker crust.
Add your favorite toppings.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in medium sized saucepan; remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Cool; add egg and vanilla; beat by hand. Add sifted (or stirred) dry ingredients all at once and stir in by hand, until well mixed.
Spread in lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes; do not overbake.
Cool and cut in desired size.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the flour, cornmeal, cornstarch, salt, paprika, dried oregano, sage, and pepper.
In a shallow bowl, beat eggs and water.
Dip the chicken in egg mixture and then place in the bag a few at a time, and shake until coated.

title: corn bread or muffins
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cornmeal.
Beat eggs slightly, add milk and oleo.
Combine with dry ingredients, stirring only until mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut bars
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of bars.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Spread the chocolate evenly to make the topping.

title: southwestern dip
directions: Chop onions including green stems, bell pepper and diced tomatoes.
Combine with beans and cheese.
Just before serving, add crushed corn chips and dressing.
Mix well.

title: grandma's nut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Work in Crisco and oleo.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Add walnuts to dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg mixture; beat well.
Let stand 25 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: hearty potato ham chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Melt butter in saucepan; add pepper and onion.
Saute until tender.
Add potatoes and 2 cups water with seasonings.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender. Make paste of flour and 1/3 cup water; add to potatoes.
Add milk and cook until slightly thickened.
Stir in undrained corn and ham.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Saute sausage, celery and onion.
In large bowl, combine sausage mix and remaining ingredients; blend well.
Stuff into bird and roast according to standard roasting directions.
Mixture may also be baked in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for one hour or until lightly browned.
Makes about 12 cups or 10 to 12 servings.

title: seafoam nut kisses
directions: With electric mixer at high speed, beat egg white, milk and water in a small bowl until stiff.
Beat in brown sugar, one tablespoon at a time, to make a thick, glossy, meringue-like mixture.
Scrape sides of bowl often.

title: spinach-stuffed steaks
directions: If using fresh spinach, cook 15 to 20 minutes in one cup water until tender.
Drain water off.
Mix together first four ingredients.
Set aside.
Split each steak from outer edge toward bone, making a pocket.
Divide spinach mixture; fill each steak. Melt butter in skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat, turning once, until desired doneness.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and add topping.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; knead 10 minutes. Let rise until double in bulk. Cut small pieces. Stretch until round and flatten. Make hole in center and let rise again, 10 minutes or more. Deep fry. Makes 25 pieces.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook the Minute rice and brown the onion and butter together. Add all ingredients together and cook in wok.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hands.
Form into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: sue's dressing
directions: Make cornbread and crumble with toast.
Mix green onions and celery; cook in small amount of water until tender.
Add celery and onion mix, eggs and butter to cornbread.
Use enough broth to moisten; salt and pepper to taste.
Heat, uncovered, 30 minutes at 375°.

title: fast fruit cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder in a 2-quart baking dish.
Stir in milk and vanilla to make a thin batter.
Place fruit slices over the batter and drizzle the melted butter over the top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes according to depth of dish or until nicely browned.
Try berries or fruit in season.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until warm through.

title: brown and serve sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make 8 patties, 2 ounces each. Use a nonstick pan and brown on both sides.
Serve with sauteed green peppers and onions.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Do ahead of time and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Pour dressing on and toss at the very last minute.
Sprinkle on bacon bits.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix; divide in 1/2.
Place on sheet of tinfoil.
Shape in rolls.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Take out of refrigerator and unwrap.
Take out of foil; lay on wire rack.
Place rack on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour.
Re-wrap; place in refrigerator or freezer.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut into thin slices.
Combine all other ingredients and shake well.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate for a while.
Stir well when ready to serve.

title: braised short ribs of beef
directions: Dredge each piece of beef with seasoned flour.
Brown in a little oil in a skillet.
Remove to casserole.
Add remaining ingredients to drippings in the skillet, stirring until well blended and pour over meat.
Cover and roast in a 350° oven for about 2 hours or until tender.
If desired, vegetables such as potatoes, sliced carrots or turnip may be added for the last half hour of roasting.
Add more water if necessary.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of baking dish.
Spread 1 can refried beans on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle onions over the beans.
(If desired, you can spread salsa over the beans also.)
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° until cheese on top is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamy pralines(club member: renee evans)
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and butter. Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Add pecans and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove; let set 5 minutes. Stir rapidly until mixture begins to coat pecans and thickens. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper or aluminum foil.

title: blue whistler burger
directions: Prepare medium hot grill. Place ground beef in large bowl. Set aside. In medium bowl, blend butter with all remaining ingredients, except sandwich buns. Reserve about 4 teaspoons seasoned butter for buns. Blend remaining butter mixture thoroughly into ground beef. Form into 4 (1-inch) thick patties. Grill burgers over medium-hot fire until done, about 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Butter buns. Grill about 1 minute, buttered side down.

title: spinach pie
directions: Slice onions.
Prepare pie crust.
Blend spinach, cottage cheese and onions; mix and heat in microwave for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs; save aside 1 teaspoon of eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour into pie crust.
Put top crust on.
Add 1 teaspoon of water to eggs; spread on top of pie crust.
Bake until golden brown.
Yum yum!

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and cream
cheese.
Add
sugar
and
cream thoroughly.
Add eggs one at
a
time, beating well after each. Add vanilla and almond.
Add
flour
1/3 cup at a time, beating well after each addition. Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tasty broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can double and triple.
Don't add too much mushroom soup.
Tastes great.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Combine soup and milk and heat thoroughly.
Toss vegetables and soup mix and serve hot. Variation:
May add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Combine cracker crumbs, confectioners sugar and shortening and mix well.

title: brown bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water; let stand 15 minutes.
Add remaining water, salt, molasses, sugar and shortening.
Add enough flour to make a soft sponge.
Beat thoroughly for about 10 minutes.
Add rest of flour.
Knead.
Then place in greased bowl. Cover.
Place in warm area.
When dough has doubled, knead again. Let rise.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Brush tops with melted butter.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Sift cake mix and pudding together in mixing bowl.
Make a well in center of mix.
Pour in water, oil, eggs and sour cream. Beat together real good.
Stir in chocolate chips with spoon. Bake in tube pan at 350° about 1 hour.

title: stuffing burger
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain well.
Add seasonings and mix.
Put back in skillet.
Put dry stuffing mix on top of hamburger.
Moisten with 3/4 cup water.
Cover with lid and cook on medium heat for 5 minutes.

title: easy egg and sausage puff
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate or bake immediately.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole; pour mixture into casserole.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: perfect brownies
directions: Measure into mixing bowl in order given, but do not mix until all are in bowl.
Mix well and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased or sprayed) for 30 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: coconut pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add sugar and stir.
Add buttermilk, margarine and vanilla.
Mix. Stir in coconut and pour in pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quiche noel
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish or pie pan with pastry; trim excess pastry around edges.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 400°
for 3 minutes, remove from oven and gently prick with a fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Let cool on rack. Sprinkle chicken, cheese, green pepper and pimento in prepared pastry shell.
Combine remaining ingredients, beating well.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 425°
for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 1 (9-inch) quiche.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Melt margarine with salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and microwave for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over and add mushrooms. Microwave for 5 minutes.
Top with Durkee onion rings.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Add brick of shredded Monterey Jack cheese. Microwave again until cheese melts.

title: chicken broccoli orientale
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken, 1/2 at a time, until browned.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
tags: Campbell's chicken flavor Ramen noodle soup

title: chocolate chip cheese ball(appetizer or dessert)
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar until smooth. Stir in chocolate chips, 1/4 cup of pecans can also be stirred in. Chill 1 hour.
Form into balls and roll in remaining pecans to cover.
Serve with Nilla wafers, graham crackers or other crisp cookies.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix everything together and pour into a buttered casserole dish (1 1/2-quart).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients together in small bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients in large bowl, then add yeast mixture.
Add 10 or more cups Occident flour, enough to make a stiff dough yet easy to knead.
Knead well.
Let rise until double in size.
Knead again. Let rise again.
Knead again and divide into 5 large loaf pans or 6 small ones.
Let rise until double and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican pinto beans
directions: In large kettle, add ingredients.
On medium heat, cook until boiling.
Turn down heat to low.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours; stir occasionally.
(Done when beans are tender.)
Ten minutes before serving, take a potato masher and mash beans slightly to thicken sauce.
Stir and serve.

title: leslie's delight
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown ground beef, garlic, onion and green pepper in the margarine.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and sugar.
In separate bowl, blend cream cheese, sour cream and cottage cheese.
In greased 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer half the cooked noodles, then cheese mixture and last, the rest of the noodles.
Cover with ground beef mixture. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick fudge
directions: Stir together over low heat until melted together. Gradually increase heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from stove. Add vanilla to hot fudge. Pour into a mixing bowl. Beat until cool. Pour onto a buttered dish.

title: porcupines
directions: Combine hamburger, rice, soup mix, Worcestershire sauce, parsley, mint, oregano and 1/4 can soup.
Shape into 2-inch mounds (I use an ice cream scoop, so they will be uniform.)
Place in baking dish; bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until pink color is gone.
Drain fat from pan.

title: chicken 'n dressing bake
directions: Toss stuffing with 1/2 can of the soup, broth and eggs. Spread in a greased 7 x 11-inch dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine remaining soup with milk and pimento; pour over all.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until set.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, salt, powder and soda.
Add flour and mix well.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Mix all together.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: upside down chocolate cake
directions: Pam an oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle in nuts.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over nuts.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo.
Spoon this
mixture in blob over cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or so.
Looks not done, but is.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chippers
directions: Place oats in food processor bowl or container of electric blender; process until finely ground.
Set aside.
Cream butter. Gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add whole egg and vanilla, beating well.
Combine ground oats, flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels.

title: zesty cheese ball
directions: Blend together all ingredients until smooth.
Chill until able to handle and roll into a ball.
Roll ball in paprika and/or cracker pepper.
Also, a good stuffing for vegetables.

title: 2 hour rolls(easy)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add boiling water and salt.
Add yeast mixture; stir.
Add 3 cups flour; mix well.
Add 3 cups more flour; dough will be moist.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Spread margarine over crackers and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: southwestern-style spaghetti squash
directions: Halve squash; discard seeds.
Place, cut side down, in 1 (12 x 7 x 2-inch) microwave-safe dish.
Add 2 tablespoons of water to dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and microcook on 100% (High) for 15 to 20 minutes (lower wattage oven 20 to 25 minutes) or until tender, rearranging once.
Drain; set aside.

title: real italian spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and pork.
Drain meat by putting on paper towels and soaking up as much of the grease as possible.
Mix tomato sauce and paste.
Add spices, onion and mushrooms; simmer for 55 minutes.
Add cheese and simmer for another 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: spritzy tuna salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni as directed on package.
Mash tuna with a fork; add mayonnaise, pickle relish, mustard, sugar, pepper, eggs and onion.
Mix well.
With plastic or wooden spoon, mix in macaroni noodles until they are covered in tuna mixture.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken pie
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Place soup, chicken, vegetables and stock on bottom.
Mix flour and milk in melted margarine.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together and spread 2 rounded tablespoons of mixture on each piece of chicken.
Fasten chicken together with toothpicks.
Place toothpick side up in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt oleo and pour over the bundles. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 3 cups; set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and ginger in saucepan; gradually stir in reserved juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add the green pepper, onion, carrots and chicken.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve over rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt butter; add dates, sugar and coconut.
Cook 6 minutes, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Remove from heat and cool. Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: happy bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, flour, nuts and chips.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and spread batter in pan. (Batter will be thick.)
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
(Do not overbake!)
Coconut may be added to batter.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer cracker crumbs, sliced zucchini, sliced tomato, sliced onion, salt and pepper. Top with cheese and bacon.

title: deluxe chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Place rack in center of oven and heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 12-cup Bundt pan or 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans; dust lightly with flour.

title: turkey-n-vegetable chowder
directions: Cook turkey until done.
Save broth.
Cut turkey into pieces. Take broth and add water to make 10 cups.
Place chopped celery, carrots and salt and pepper in broth.
Simmer while chopping other ingredients.
Add onion, basil, potatoes and corn and simmer, covered, for 25 minutes.
Make sure vegetables are tender, then add meat and simmer until meat is hot.
Put flour in medium bowl and stir in milk using wire whisk until no lumps remain.
Pour into soup, stirring constantly, until soup comes to a boil.
Stir in cheese and cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly and soup thickens.
Pour into a soup bowl and sprinkle with parsley.

title: country breakfast
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
(Add more salt or pepper to taste.)
Dust tenderloin in flour mixture.
Fry pieces of tenderloin in a little oil over medium heat until meat is done as desired.
Remove tenderloin from skillet.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender (pressure cooker speeds time). Remove chicken from bones.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cauliflower with huntingdon sauce
directions: Trim cauliflower; place in pot of boiling water.
Cover; simmer 3 to 4 minutes.

title: far east chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked and cut up chicken in buttered baking dish.
Mix soup, vegetables, noodles and soy sauce; spread over chicken.
Top with cashews.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: homemade peanut butter spread (with a twist)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a food processor until crumbly.
Add olive oil, 1 teaspoon at a time, until you reach desired consistency.

title: first prize mustard pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers, green tomatoes, cauliflower, celery and peppers into pieces large enough to be distinguished.
Onions are to be peeled and put in whole.
Let set overnight in 2/3 cup salt.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: very good german chocolate cake
directions: Grease bottom of pan.
Put coconut and nuts in bottom of pan. Make cake mix following box directions.
Pour into pan.
Mix other ingredients and spread over top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, macaroni and 1 cup water. Simmer until macaroni is tender.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place raw, cut-up rhubarb.
Combine sugar and dry strawberry jello and sprinkle over rhubarb.
Next, pour yellow cake mix on rhubarb and pour water over dry mixture. Then melt margarine and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Do not stir anything.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Blend together crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken in melted margarine and then in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken in shallow dish or pan.
Pour the rest of the butter and crumbs over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn temperature down if it gets too brown.

title: indian pudding(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine cornmeal and 1 cup of the milk in small bowl; let rest 15 minutes.
Heat rest of milk in saucepan (do not boil).
Remove; add cornmeal mixture and remaining ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings total.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions.
Rinse black beans in a colander.
Saute onion until soft in olive oil.
Add celery and red or green pepper and garlic.
Cook only until slightly soft.
Add cooked rice, tomatoes, black beans and any optional ingredients desired.
Put into casserole dish, sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese is melted. This is a great side dish or terrific filling for burritos.
Just add salsa, lettuce, tomato and sour cream.

title: butterscotch sundae sauce
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and butter in heavy saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat; let cool 5 minutes.
Add rum and half and half, stirring well.
Serve sauce warm over ice cream or pound cake.
Yields 1 cup.

title: veg beef soup
directions: Brown beef (sprinkle salt into dry pan before adding raw beef).
Add all the other ingredients.
Cook until potatoes and turnips are done.
Serve.

title: fish bisque
directions: To make white sauce, in a medium saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour and salt until smooth.
