Gradually add milk, pepper and green onion.
Heat until sauce is bubbling and starting to thicken, stirring occasionally.
Add onion dip and stir.
Fold in cooked fish.
Simmer until fish is warmed.
More milk may be added to thin bisque.
Serve over rice, wide noodles or biscuits.

title: special cheese cake
directions: Mix these ingredients together and set aside.

title: foolproof chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with milk. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store in an airtight container.

title: apple raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, Dannon nonfat or low-fat yogurt, milk, margarine and egg product; let stand for 5 minutes.
In a bowl, blend flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in bran mixture just until blended.
Stir in apples and raisins.
Spoon batter into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix in bowl until blended.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In a 2-quart casserole, add soup, beans, hamburger and onion.
Mix cornbread as directed on box and spoon over beef mixture.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sloppy joes("great for sunday dinners on cold winter evenings.)
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet until juicy.
Add other ingredients and simmer slower until meat is done.
Serve on buns. Makes 4 servings.

title: curry dip
directions: Add first 5 ingredients to mayo.
Stir, blend and chill.

title: garden-stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops from peppers.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cook peppers in boiling, salted water 3 to 5 minutes.
Invert to drain.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and set aside.
Cook the pumpkin, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, salt and cinnamon until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Cool.
Beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour over cooled baked crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: lo-cal tuna pasta salad
directions: In mixing bowl, place tuna (drained), noodles, onion, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Add Italian dressing slowly.
Too much will make the salad tart.
Stir mixture and place in refrigerator. Mix occasionally before serving.
Serves two.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
In large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, beat milk, peanut butter, salad oil and eggs until smooth.
Stir peanut butter mixture into flour mixture just until moistened (do not overmix or muffins will be tough; batter should be lumpy).
Stir in raisins.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin pan cups, filling each cup about 2/3 full.
Bake muffins 20 minutes or until well risen and golden and toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean and dry.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish; mix well.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until golden brown and crusty on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Preheat your skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.
Mix all ingredients together, stirring well.
Place into greased skillet.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes and top is golden brown.
Serve with margarine on each slice, while hot.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg to make sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add butter.
Pare and core apples.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once.
Stir fast until flour is moistened.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut six 5-inch squares.
Place 1 apple on each square; dot with butter.
Fold corners and pinch edges.
Place 1 inch apart in greased pan.
Pour sauce over dumplings.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: oyster cocktail
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and marinate oysters in it. Chill. Cut grapefruit in half. Remove the core and loosen the sections. Place 2 oysters in center of each grapefruit half.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan and set aside.
Thoroughly combine the strawberries and syrup with the gelatin and set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and put in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Then dump into the pan the undrained pineapple.
Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit and sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Slice the butter thinly and lay on top to cover.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix by hand and
bake in 13 x 9-inch pan, ungreased, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper pot stew
directions: Cover the chicken with water, bring to a boil, reduce the heat and simmer for 45 minutes, skimming off any form that forms. Remove the chicken and reserve the broth.
Remove the chicken meat from the bone and chop.
Brown the pork or beef in the oil.
Add the onions and saute until soft.
Combine all the ingredients, except the vinegar, in the broth and simmer for an hour or until the meat is very tender and the stew is thick.
Stir in the vinegar and serve.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender, not browned.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup to make a sauce.
Put drained hominy in baking dish and pour sauce over hominy.
Put a handful of crushed Fritos on top and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: japanese rice
directions: Add everything together and cook until hot.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp-guacamole dip
directions: Thaw dip and shrimp according to package directions.
In a bowl, combine dip and lemon juice.
Gently stir in chopped tomato. Transfer to shallow serving bowl; put dollop of sour cream atop avocado mixture.
With a narrow spatula, swirl sour cream through avocado mixture to marble.
Arrange shrimp atop dip.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve with vegetable dippers.
Makes 16 servings.

title: spiced honey orange vinaigrette
directions: Combine ingredients in jar and shake vigorously.
Serve over fruit or green salad.

title: fried dough
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until very warm.
Gradually add to flour mixture and beat thoroughly.
Stir in additional flour to form a soft dough. Turn out onto a lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise until size doubles.
Heat vegetable oil to 375°.
Cut pieces of dough to desired size.
Stretch out and drop into hot shortening.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Brush with melted butter.
Add desired toppings.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and oleo.
Put into baking dish and sprinkle crackers and oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken-rice skillet dinner
directions: Fry chicken in large skillet until nicely browned.
Add remainder of ingredients; let simmer for 1 hour, until all liquid has evaporated and chicken is done.
Cover while cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: scalloped cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower (chop into pieces). Combine egg, 1/2 cup of the crumbs, soup, cheese, onion and salt. Then stir in the cauliflower. Put into casserole dish. Combine remaining cup of bread crumbs and melted margarine. Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add cake mix (dry) about 1/3 at a time, mixing well.
(Cover; chill about 30 minutes.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown at 375°.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake by package directions for a 9 x 13-inch cake.
Prick top with a fork and pour Kahlua over the cake.
Let this soak in; should be left overnight.
Make chocolate mousse according to directions.

title: opal's quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine milk and flour, mixing well.
Add yeast and remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Leave in mixing bowl to rise until doubled in bulk. Then roll out like biscuit dough, make into rolls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: no crust quiche
directions: Thaw broccoli and press out all liquid.
Mix together broccoli, onion, green pepper, Cheddar cheese and ham.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat until smooth milk, eggs, salt, pepper and Bisquick mix.
Pour over the first layer.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 400° preheated oven or until a silver knife inserted comes out clean.

title: whole wheat honey bread
directions: Measure all-purpose flour and whole wheat flour into a bowl; stir to mix.
Set aside.
Combine warm water, shortening, dry milk, yeast, honey, salt and 3 cups of flour mixture in largest mixer bowl.
Mix well on low speed, scraping sides and bottom of bowl often.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually stir in remaining flour by hand to make a very stiff dough.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter and mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish and top with a thin layer of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: international coffee
directions: Mix the three dry ingredients in a blender for 1 to 2 minutes. Store in an airtight container.
To serve, place 2 heaping teaspoonfuls in a cup.
Pour in boiling water; stir.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Mix together cranberries, apples, grapes, sugar and nut meats.
Set aside.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Soften ice cream and add first 6 ingredients.
Mix well (use mixer).
When smooth, pour into pie shells.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before slicing.
Can be made several days ahead and kept in freezer.

title: amish chicken noodle soup
directions: Place chicken in a kettle with 2 qts. of water, cover until tender (about 2 1/2 hrs). Remove chicken from the kettle and strain the broth.
Debone the chicken and return to the kettle with the strained broth.
Add chicken stock, celery, carrots, apple, onions and pepper and cook until vegetables are tender. Add noodles and cook another 8-10 minutes.

title: hot milk sponge cake(a moist and easy cake to make.)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs with sugar; add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Heat milk and butter (do not boil) and add to batter.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Add seasoning.
Boil this all together for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, then thicken with 3 tablespoons Clear Jell and cold pack for 20 minutes. This is also good to make spaghetti and Sloppy Joes.

title: swamp balls
directions: Prepare spinach according to package directions. Drain and press down to remove moisture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine sugar, salt, spices and 1/2 cup water in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring to 238° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add walnuts; stir gently until mixture becomes creamy.
Turn onto waxed paper.
With fork, separate nuts.
Let dry.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cool lemon chicken salad
directions: Mix dressing, juice and peel.
Add all other ingredients. Chill 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: german chocolate caramel cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool completely.
Poke large holes in cake.
Mix together caramel topping and sweetened condensed milk.
Pour over cake.
Blend softened cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until blended. Spread over cake and sprinkle with toffee bits.
Refrigerate.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased and floured cake pans.

title: eggplant upside down pie
directions: Preheat broiler.
Grease bottom and sides of 10-inch pie plate with 1 1/2 teaspoon olive oil.
Dust with bread crumbs.
Place eggplant on a baking sheet; brush both sides with 1/4 cup oil. Broil about 5 minutes or until lightly browned on both sides. Reduce oven to 350°.
Cook rice following package directions. Salt.
Drain excess liquid.
Reserve rice.

title: cocoa drops
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Bake at 400°.
Drop with teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Frost with butter icing.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash button mushrooms in cold water; drain them and drop them into boiling, salted water.
Simmer the mushrooms for 5 minutes, without boiling.
Drain them and cover the mushrooms with cold water.
Drain the mushrooms and put them in a mixing bowl.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually; beat in milk and flavoring.
Fold in snow and eat immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup together.
Arrange broccoli on the bottom of square Pyrex pan or Corning Ware pan. Pour half of sour cream mixture over broccoli.
Put chicken on top of the broccoli.
Put the rest of the sour cream mixture on top of the chicken.
Top each chicken breast with Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Bake until it bubbles and the cheese is golden brown.
Serve with rice.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and serve on crackers.

title: chinese chews
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Add pecans and stir into mixture.
Pour in well-greased cake pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Test for doneness.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: white chili
directions: Place beans, broth, garlic and 1 1/2 onions into soup pot. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until beans are soft (2 to 3 hours).
Add more broth, if needed.
In a skillet, saute remaining onion and seasonings.
When onions are soft, add to beans.
Add chicken.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: great-grandmother minnie's rolls
directions: In a bowl, sift the flour.
In a separate bowl, dissolve the yeast in 3 tablespoons of warm water.
Add the lukewarm water, shortening, sugar and egg.
Slowly add the flour, blending well. Refrigerate overnight.
Shape the dough into rolls and let the rolls rise in a warm place.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned. Makes 3 dozen.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Cook over medium heat for 1 minute.
Pour into 2 sets of Tupperware ice cups and freeze.

title: curried fruit
directions: Note:
Mix or match fruits to your personal taste.

title: vegetable puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot fat and cook until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 8 puffs.

title: blt dip
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, then crumble.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, bacon and diced tomato.
Toast bread, then cut into bite size pieces (about 6 to 8 pieces per slice).
Bread can be toasted ahead of time, but keep sealed in a plastic container.
Dip toast pieces into dip and enjoy.

title: hot country style biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt in large bowl.
Cut in shortening with fork or pastry blender until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Combine milk and lemon juice, then add to flour mixture.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick and cut out with dough or round cookie cutter.
Place close together in greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until tops are golden.
Brush with melted butter when done.
Makes about 15 biscuits.

title: cherry in snow
directions: Cut angel food cake into thin slices.
Layer in pan.
Whip Dream Whip until smooth.
Whip Dream Whip, cream cheese and vanilla together.
Put layer of cheese mixture on first layer of cake.
Repeat layers.
Top with can of cherry pie filling.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Use glass Pyrex dish, approximately 9 x 13 inch.
Set lime Jello first per pkg. instructions.
Put 2 cups hot water in lemon Jello, add marshmallows, cream cheese and sugar (if using whipping cream).
When cool add pineapple and whipped cream.
When partially set, pour mixture on top of lime Jello.
When this mixture has set, pour partially set cherry Jello on top.
Serve when fully set.

title: quick and easy creamy fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, buttermilk and Cool Whip with a wire whip.
Add fruit.
Chill before serving.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: blueberry and peach shortcake
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in 1/3 cup ReaLemon brand and vanilla.
Spread on cake; chill.
In small saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, water and 1 tablespoon ReaLemon brand.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add blueberries; cook until bubbly.
Chill. Before serving, top cake with peach slices and blueberry sauce. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Make into balls, putting on cookie sheet and pressing down with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
They should not turn brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in shortening.
Combine the other ingredients and pour over meat.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve on buns. Yields 8 Sloppy Joes.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: Cook tortellini according to directions in salted water.
While tortellini are cooking, beat egg yolks lightly with a fork and add to cream.
Melt butter.
Place drained, hot tortellini in warm serving bowl or platter.
Pour on egg and cream mixture, melted butter and about 1/2 of grated cheese.
Toss tortellini with a fork and spoon until well blended, adding more cheese as desired.
Top with additional grated cheese and serve immediately.

title: blueberry-banana morning drink
directions: Peel banana.
Cut into 6 chunks and wrap with plastic wrap. Freeze overnight.
Following day, put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: chicken
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with beef.
Place breast on top (can be rolled in bacon strips).
Cover with soup and sour cream mixture.
Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: basic recipe - meats and vegetables baby food
directions: Put ingredients into blender (mini).
Process at puree until smooth.
Add full amount of liquid for very young babies; decrease amount as child grows older.
Freeze in ice cube trays until needed.

title: cranapple sauce
directions: In a saucepan bring first three ingredients to a boil.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until sugar is dissolved and cranberries break open.
Refrigerate overnight.
Can be reheated.
Great with roast, pork or chicken.

title: toaster oatmeal cookies
directions: Spread dry oats on a jelly roll pan and put under the broiler to toast. Stir frequently to brown evenly and watch because they burn quickly. Set toasted oats aside.
Cream together the shortening and the sugars. Add eggs and blend.
Add toasted oats and mix well. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Blend.
Drop by large rounded spoonful for man-sized cookies. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes
or until dry. Don't overbake. Bake less time for smaller cookies.

title: grandma brooks' no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients (sugar, cocoa, milk and butter) to a full boil in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm, preferably in a refrigerator.
Makes approximately 30 cookies.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook veggies as indicated on package.
Drain.
Mix vegetables together into a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Melt Velveeta and 1 stick of butter together.
Pour over vegetables.
Melt rest of butter and mix with crumbled crackers.
Spread/sprinkle over cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake 20 minutes.

title: hearty tuna salad
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Drain and cool. Combine beans, tuna, celery, mayo or salad dressing, lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Chill.
Before serving, add chow mein noodles and toss lightly.
Serve in lettuce cups or in small, pretty bowls.
Serves 4.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter together until creamy. Add sugar, melted chocolate squares, vanilla and pecans. Put in 8 x 8-inch buttered glass dish. Let it set and cut into squares.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat strawberry cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with strawberries.
You can use fresh strawberries (1 pint), mixed in with ingredients.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, in 2 cups cold water, until tender.
Add sugar and cook 5 minutes. While the cranberries are cooking, soften the gelatin in 1 cup of cold water; add to hot cranberry mixture along with scant 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After it has chilled, add 1 cup chopped nuts and the celery.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown meat and diced onions in skillet; pour off grease. Place in 5-quart pan.
Add kidney beans, then rinse out can and add to meat.
Add tomato sauce, then rinse cans and add to meat until ingredients rise to top of pan.
Add salt, pepper and sugar; bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer.
Stir frequently.
Simmer approximately 3 to 4 hours.

title: coffee sorbet
directions: Stir every hour or so until serving.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: jalapeno pepper appetizers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise; remove seeds, stems and center membrane. Stuff each half with about 2 teaspoons of cream cheese. Wrap with bacon and secure with a toothpick. Place on a broiler rack that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Remove toothpicks. Serve immediately. Yield: 20 appetizers.

title: green beans delicious
directions: Cook beans and onion salt 20 minutes.
Make sauce of remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese melts.
Drain beans.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of beans and sauce with sauce as top layer.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake batter as directed on box.
Pour half of cake batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Layer broccoli, cauliflower and green onion.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and raisins.
Combine sugar and mayonnaise.
Pour over salad.
Make the night before.

title: vegetable saute
directions: Melt
margarine in a 10-inch Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook
and	stir
until onion is tender.
Add zucchini and mushrooms.
Cook
12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, salt, oregano and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Crumble sausage.
Cool and drain.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° until knife blade comes out clean when inserted in middle, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco sauce
directions: In blender, combine ingredients and blend 3 minutes.
Enough for 12 tacos.

title: low-fat fried rice
directions: Pour soup and margarine on top of rice.
Microwave on High 15 to 20 minutes in glass container.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk for 30 minutes.
Combine the remaining ingredients together in a bowl.
Beat egg; add to oatmeal mixture and to dry mixture all at once.
Stir enough to mix.
Batter is not supposed to look smooth.
Grease muffin tins well; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: savory fruit dip
directions: In a food processor or blender, combine all 3 ingredients until smooth.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dip. Serve at room temperature with fruit and cheese platter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken in small pieces. Melt margarine. Pour over dressing mix. Mix together 2 cups chicken broth and both cans soup. Make layers of dressing mix and layer of chicken. Pour soup mixture over after each layer. Top off with dressing. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: easy casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: puffy-crunchy shrimp batter
directions: Measure out dry ingredients into mixing bowl; add liquids a little at a time until the mixture is smooth and thick. Dip shrimp, fry and feast!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a pan.
Place on medium heat and stir.
In a few minutes, drop some in cold water and if it forms a ball, take from stove and add vanilla, peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until cool, pour in platter. Cut when cool.
"Good."

title: fresh salsa(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Hint: Wear rubber gloves to handle and chop jalapeno peppers.

title: girdle buster
directions: Mix together.
Pour this mixture over the first layer; spread evenly.
Bake approximately 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 can mushroom soup with the other ingredients.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, firmly shape in a large loaf.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.
In medium bowl, combine remaining soup and 1/2 cup water.
Heat over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour over meat loaf and cook 30 minutes more.

title: pickled eggs and hot peppers
directions: Choose young tender pods of okra, no more than 3-inches long. Wash and place in a colander. Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Dip colander into boiling water for 1 minute to blanch okra. Drain well. Pack okra in sterile jars with stem up. Prepare Vinegar Spice Mixture and pour over okra. Seal lids and water bath for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix Duncan Hines according to package.
Mix Polly-O, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add chips to Polly-O mixture and add Duncan Hines.
Bake according to package directions.

title: holiday nuggets
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cream thoroughly shortening, butter and sugar.
Blend in vanilla, almond extract and nuts.
Add gradually dry ingredients; mix until dough is smooth and well blended.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 25 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar while cookies are still hot.

title: apple and cranberry pie
directions: Make crust for a 2-crust pie, using shortening, flour, salt and cold water.
Fill pie with apples, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cooked fresh cranberries.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a cup.
Stir in hot milk to fill cup.
Add vanilla.
Stir until blended.

title: crustless egg pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix until well blended and very soupy.
Stir and bake in 2 greased pie pans.
Bake at 345° to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in nonaluminum bowl.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt the butter and pour over batter.
Add fruit and sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake at 375° until done.
Quick and easy and oh, so good!

title: baked bay scallops
directions: Melt butter in pan and add mushrooms.
Cook, stirring, until wilted.
Add onion and garlic until transparent.
Transfer mixture to bowl; add 2 tablespoons butter and everything else.
Spoon into baking dish.
Drizzle remaining butter on top.
Bake 10 minutes in 450° oven and broil 1 minute to brown.
(Do not overcook.)
Can be made ahead and frozen before baking.
Serves 6.

title: chicken-okra gumbo(cajun style)
directions: Cook rice in 4 cups of water.
Set aside.
Boil chicken in 10 or 12-quart soup pot until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and debone.
Return chicken to pot.
In another pot, put 3 tablespoons oil, sliced okra, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Cook until smothered down, stirring constantly.
When done, add to the chicken and broth, stirring constantly.
Watch closely as it will boil over if not stirred constantly.
Simmer about 2 hours.
When almost done, add gumbo file.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve in soup bowl over rice.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Lay half of the pork chops in pan.
Salt and pepper chops.
Mix the "Catherine Clark" dressing as directed and spread in pan.
Cover dressing with the remaining pork chops.
Add 2 cans chicken-mushroom soup diluted with a little less than 2 cans of milk (about 1 1/2 cans).
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: 7-up sausage
directions: Put sausage in frying pan.
Pour 7-Up over the sausage.
Cook on low heat; stir occasionally.
Reduce 7-Up completely.
Sausage will have a glaze look.
Good served with creamed potatoes and a green vegetable.

title: quick pepperoni spaghetti
directions: Combine onion, pepper, beef and pepperoni.
Cook until brown (drain).
Return to skillet.
Add sauce and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti (drain).
Arrange on an ovenproof platter.
Spoon meat sauce on top.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sauce.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix together and heat until blended the barbecue sauce or the mixture of lemon juice, vegetable oil, water, sugar, salt, liquid red pepper seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
Brush chicken with sauce.
Place chicken on grill, bone side down.
Grill over medium setting 45 to 60 minutes, turning every 15 minutes.
Wait until last 10 minutes to baste with sauce. Makes 4 to 8 servings. Excellent for gas grill and outside cooking.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil the chicken, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper. Remove chicken from the broth and debone.
In a large bowl with a wide bottom and sloping sides, pour flour and pack the flour around the sides of the bowl, forming a wall.
The amount of flour you use depends on how many dumplings you want.
You will still have some flour in the bottom of the bowl.
Add about 3/4 cup of broth into the center of the flour.
Gently knock some of the flour into the broth.
As it forms a dough, drop it into the remaining broth left in the pot.
Turn the fire low and let it simmer.
Continue making the dumplings with the remaining flour and broth until you think you have enough dumplings.
Stir the pot often while the dumplings are cooking or they will stick.
When the dumplings are cooked throughout, add the deboned chicken and stir.
Serve while hot.

title: bay seafood seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in an airtight container.
Use on seafood or chicken.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine mushrooms, water chestnuts, soup mix and water in skillet.
Heat until hot.
Add mixture to cooked broccoli in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.
Contains approximately 120 calories each.
Serves 6.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Cut a pumpkin in half and remove all seeds and membranes.
(If you plan to make toasted pumpkin seeds, wash the seeds and place them on a paper towel to dry.)
Peel the outside and cut into small chunks.
Place these in a large pot and cover with water.
Boil until pumpkin is tender.
Drain off water and mash pumpkin.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Pour in greased container.

title: egg rolls
directions: Swirl two tablespoons of oil in a hot wok or skillet.
Add cabbage and celery; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Remove pan from heat. Add the pork, shrimp, scallions, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix; fill rolls.
Roll and seal with egg.
Let rolls rest 1 hour on oiled wax paper. Heat wok or skillet.
Fry rolls in 3 cups of oil; drain and keep warm until ready to serve.
Serve with mustard and sweet and sour sauce.
Yield: 10 servings.
Carbohydrate 17 g, protein 9 g, fat 11 g, calories 203.
One serving = 1 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix and milk.
Add other ingredients in order given; mix well.
Pour into 3 greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and mix. Add cereal and mix. Press in 9 x 13 pan. Melt chips and spread over top.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Grease 8 or 9-inch round cake pan.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
(Dough will be extremely sticky.)
Put dough into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: tasty taco salad
directions: Cook beef until browned, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle taco seasoning and onion soup mix over beef.
Add water; stir to mix. Simmer over low flame for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding, milk, pumpkin and spices in a large bowl.
Heat on low speed 1 minute.
Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell and chill.

title: rhubarb marmalade
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces.
Cover with sugar and let stand overnight.
Grind the orange rinds and raisins.
Add the orange juice.
Let simmer for 3 or 4 hours and pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Stir mixture to prevent burning or scorching.

title: fruit ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fruit.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1-gallon freezer.
Freeze to a mush according to manufacturer's instructions.
Add fruit and freeze a few minutes longer.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli in seperate pans according to thier pkg. directions.
Lightly saute celery and onions.
Set aside. Mix the hot rice with the Cheez Whiz and oleo.

title: diabetic chicken salad
directions: Dice chicken, apples and celery.
Mix together and add raisins. Chill.
Mix lemon juice and mayonnaise. Pour over salad and toss.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Cut bacon in half.
Cut crust off bread.
Spread soup onto bread.
Cut bread into thirds.
Lay the cut bread on top of the cut bacon.
Roll the bacon over the bread forming a tight roll. Secure with a toothpick.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into small pieces.
Add the onions, tomatoes and mushrooms over top of spinach.
Sprinkle with wheat germ.
Serve with favorite salad dressing.

title: banana split cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 10 inch bundt pan. Cream together sugar and oil; add eggs, vanilla, and buttermilk; Mix just until blended (don't over mix). Blend in bananas.

title: corn flake balls
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Bring to a full boil and remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes, stirring until completely coated.
With wet hands, roll into balls.
Place onto cookie sheet, wax paper or foil until cool.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl mix first chicken, soups, salsa and onion.
In large casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan, layer chicken mixture, cheese and tortillas.
Repeat layers ending with cheese. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in uncovered dish.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening or butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and egg.
Add flour, baking soda and salt. (Sift together and add to the creamed mixture.)
Roll into balls and press with fork. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cast-iron skillet cornbread
directions: Coat bottom and sides of 10-inch cast-iron skillet with bacon drippings; heat in a 450° oven. Whisk together buttermilk and egg. Add cornmeal,
stirring well; whisk in baking powder, soda and salt. Pour batter into hot skillet. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until cornbread is golden.

title: baked macaroni
directions: In saucepan, boil macaroni until done.
Drain water off macaroni.
In bowl, mix eggs, sugar, salt and milk.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, put macaroni; pour egg mixture over macaroni.
Pour melted butter over macaroni.
Bake in 350° oven about an hour.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Prepare zucchini; combine with salt and other vegetables. Allow mixture to stand overnight.
Drain, rinse thoroughly and drain again in a colander.
Press bowl down on top of vegetable mixture to force out as much liquid as possible.
In a large enamel pot, combine remaining ingredients, add vegetables and bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently 20 minutes.
Ladle relish into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Grease sides and bottoms of 2 loaf pans.
Cut wax paper to fit bottom of pan (grease paper).
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Mix together crackers and melted margarine. Reserve half of cracker mixture for topping.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with reserved crackers while baking.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls in strips on greased cookie sheet and pinch edges to seal.
Bake until delicately brown (like pie crust).
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill and minced onion.
Spread on cool crust.
Top with sliced mushrooms, radishes, cucumbers, green pepper, tomatoes, green and/or black olives, onion, grated cheese or whatever combination you like.

title: brown stew
directions: In Dutch oven, thoroughly brown meat (on all sides) in cooking oil, turning often.
Add 2 cups boiling water and next 10 ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: christmas logs
directions: Cook in a heavy skillet over low heat until dates are mushy. Remove from heat and add 1 egg, beaten with 1 cup light brown sugar.
Put on heat and stir until bubbly; stir
in 2 cups Rice Krispies and nuts.
Also stir in vanilla.

title: meat balls with a college education
directions: Mix meat, egg, salt, pepper and onion.
Form balls.
Roll in flour.
Fry until light brown.
Add 1/3 cup chicken stock, oil, pineapple and green pepper.
Simmer over low heat until peppers are tender.
Make a sauce of remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Add meat balls.
Heat thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Break ground beef into a large skillet.
Add onion; cook until beef is browned.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder, pepper sauce and mashed kidney beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Spoon a little bean mixture over bottom of 6-cup round casserole dish.
Alternate layers of tortillas and bean mixture, ending with tortillas.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into wedge shaped portions to serve.

title: maryann's fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk; bring to a boil and continue boiling for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until thick and creamy.
Add nuts if desired.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon in hot deep oil.
Will puff up and come to top when done.
May let these brown as much as you desire before taking them out of cooker.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: white frosting
directions: Blend first two ingredients well and cook until thick.
Cool, not completely.
Cream balance of ingredients well.
Combine all and beat until fluffy.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix on medium-high speed until smooth and creamy.
Use as a sour cream substitute. This sauce may be added to hot dishes by adding 1 tablespoon of cornstarch to 1 cup of sauce.
Or serve it cold with the addition of herbs or flavoring as a dressing for salad or a sauce for mousse.
Yield:
about 1 1/4 cups.

title: gingerbread
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and beat well.
Dissolve 2 level teaspoons soda in 1/8 cup hot water; add to beaten mixture.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well.
Add 1 cup boiling water and beat lightly and quickly.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt syl's cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cut in shortening.
Add orange juice, egg and orange peel to flour mixture.
Mix until just moistened.
Fold in cranberries and nuts. Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans or one large loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese and jelly - sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine and add 2 eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Add 1 cup sour cream and mix until blended.
Put 1/2 batter in a greased Bundt pan.
Dice up cream cheese in small chunks.
Press slightly into batter.
Add tablespoons of jam or jelly all around the batter as well.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use a toothpick to check doneness.
Use a drizzle frosting and enjoy.
I use almond flavoring for confectioners drizzle.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese until creamy. Add first 4 ingredients. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze until firm.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together. Add cream cheese. Soften, then add all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: millet casserole(serves 8)
directions: Boil water, millet and salt 3 minutes.
Turn heat low.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put into lecithin-prepared 8 x 8-inch baking dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn off heat and let stand 10 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 8 people.

title: circuit salad
directions: Drain fruits thoroughly.
Blend cottage cheese and dry Jell-O. Add fruits.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: casserole of okra and rice
directions: Render pieces of ham fat with ham.
Start rice cooking.
In ham drippings, fry onions, green peppers and celery.
When rice is fluffy, add okra, rice, tomatoes, garlic salt and pepper to ham mixture.
Put into casserole and bake 30 minutes in slow oven at 250°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer as listed in a large glass casserole dish. Prepare approximately 2 hours before serving. Keeps in refrigerator for several days. Serves 10-12.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat at medium speed on mixer the persimmon pulp, baking soda, sugar and margarine.
When well blended, add and continue mixing, the cloves, nutmeg, salt, cinnamon, egg, flour and nuts.

title: yakisoba
directions: *Use bell pepper, onion, green onion, cabbage, bean sprouts or water chestnuts.

title: lemon herb chicken
directions: Marinate cut up chicken in the refrigerator and grill and baste.

title: vegetable cheese bars
directions: Press crescent rolls in bottom of jelly roll pan (12 x 18-inch; larger or smaller okay).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolk until light; mix in corn, salt, Tabasco sauce and flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold in corn mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil in skillet.
Cook until browned on both sides.
Serve for breakfast with butter, syrup and bacon or as a vegetable with chicken, meat or fish at other meals. Makes about 16 to 18 fritters.

title: meat beans
directions: Cook 1 pound of beans as you usually do and when they are fairly tender, add stewed tomatoes, ground meat and onion. Continue cooking until beans are tender and meat is done.
Season with salt and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Good with cornbread.

title: frosted strawberries
directions: In a medium size bowl, combine condensed milk, coconut, 3 tablespoons gelatin, almonds, extract and enough red food coloring to tint mixture a strawberry shade.
Form small amounts (about 1/2 tablespoon) into strawberry shapes.
Sprinkle remaining gelatin into a flat dish.
Roll each strawberry in gelatin to coat.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate.
Yields 1 pound.

title: pecan spread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Fold in the sour cream. Pour into a baking dish; add chopped pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Keep warm to serve.

title: linda's salsa
directions: This is a mild sauce.
Heat it up with hot pepper sauce to taste.
Mix all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.
It is also a wonderful substitute for taco sauce, minus the black-eyed peas.
Yields 4 cups.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Cook in frypan until done.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain frozen vegetables.
Combine with soup, 1/2 cup shredded cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.
Preparation time 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orzo and vegetables
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook orzo over medium-high heat 6 minutes.
Add broccoli to pot and cook 4 to 5 minutes longer, until broccoli and orzo are tender.
Drain well. Add artichoke hearts, olives, tomatoes, scallions, oil, vinegar, garlic salt, pepper and chicken to pot, tossing well.
Serve immediately on mixed salad greens.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk, cheese and 1/4 garlic powder until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush remaining margarine and garlic powder on baked biscuits.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut a slice from top of each tomato.
Scoop out centers; mix pulp with bacon bits, celery, onion, bread crumbs, salt and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Fill centers with this mixture; sprinkle with the rest of the grated cheese.
Dot with butter; bake in greased muffin cups or baking dish for about 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well and set aside.
If using fresh broccoli, cut into large chunks, boil or steam for 5 minutes and add to mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: golden hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal and onion.
Add milk and egg, stirring well. Carefully drop batter by tablespoons into deep hot oil (375°). Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry until hush puppies are golden brown (3 to 5 minutes).
Drain well on paper towels. Makes about 2 dozen hush puppies.

title: peanut butter chocolate stars
directions: Mix peanut butter, brown sugar, and egg together until smooth.
Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Press 1 kiss into the top of each ball.
Bake 10 - 12 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: dump cake dessert
directions: Combine pineapple and pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; mix well.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread whipped topping over cooled cake.
Chill, tightly covered, until serving time.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large soup pot place bouillon cubes, bones, meat and pot herbs; cover with water.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add to pot stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Remove pot herbs, meat and bones.
Add veggies; simmer 1/2 hour more. Serves approximately 6.
Serve hot.
Tastes better next day.

title: cavitini
directions: Place cooked and drained macaroni in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix spaghetti sauce, taco sauce, ground beef and mushrooms together and pour over shells.
Top with Mozzarella and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain. Mix other ingredients and add noodles.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: * For sour milk, mix 1 tablespoon vinegar in measuring cup, then pour milk into to make 3/4 cup.

title: spaghetti pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Beat one egg; blend pasta
and 1/2 cup cheese (grated) with egg.
Line greased 10-inch deep pie dish with mixture.
Set aside.
(Forms the crust of the pie.)

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: You will need a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: 4th week soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer in large stock pot until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: macaroni-cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to instructions on box.
Drain; add butter, then other ingredients.
Top with crumbled cheese crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add seasonings to taste. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add corn and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.

title: ready hamburger mix(the beginning of many meals, made in minutes)
directions: Brown ground beef in a heavy skillet.
Drain.
Add onion and continue cooking over medium-low heat until onions are golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool.
Spoon mixture into four 1-pint freezer containers, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.
Seal and label containers.
Freeze.
Use within 3 months.
Makes about 4 pints of Ready Hamburger Mix.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oleo and water until fluffy.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; add and mix well.
Fold in nuts, chocolate chips, apples and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Top with toasted almonds.

title: sugar cream squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and margarine. Press in 9 x 13-inch cake pan, bottom and sides. Whip together 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Pour on cake mixture already pressed in pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: sugarless cherry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except pastry) in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Cool and use as you would cherry pie filling.

title: german pancakes
directions: This is best if cooked in cast-iron skillet.
Heat oven and pan to 425°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash and pick over rice.
Combine rice, milk, water, sugar, nutmeg and salt in the top of a double boiler.
Cook covered over boiling water for 2 hours or until liquid is absorbed.
Chill with cinnamon on top.

title: holiday breakfast bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, and cinnamon. Add eggs and oil; mix well. Add remaining 5 ingredients. Makes 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to an hour and 20 minutes.

title: hot cheese hors d'oeuvre
directions: Beat eggs and mix in milk.
Put a layer of shredded cheese on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then spread the 3 cans of chilies on the cheese.
Pour egg and milk on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve on crackers.

title: mom's rhubarb pie
directions: Pour slightly beaten egg yolks over rhubarb.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, tapioca and orange rind.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 30 minutes.
Make meringue of egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread on pie and return to oven to brown.

title: lasagne(serves 12)
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients for 1 minute, then add peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter melts.
Add oats, vanilla and walnuts to taste.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let cool.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Wash chicken and pat dry. Put shortening and butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place in oven to melt.

Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper. Coat chicken thoroughly with flour mixture. Place chicken, skin side down, in melted shortening. Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes. Turn and cook 30 minutes more or until fork-tender.

title: fresh florida green beans 'n ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook green beans in boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes; drain.
Combine drained beans, ham and cheese soup.
Place mixture in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter; pour over bread cubes and toss gently.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pudding wiches
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter.
Blend until smooth. Add pudding mix.
Beat with hand mixer until blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread filling between graham crackers and freeze.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs, sugar and melted margarine in 8-inch pie pan.
Remove 2 to 4 tablespoons for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture evenly into pan.

title: barberton hot sauce
directions: Brown onions and pepper in butter.
Add paprika to taste. Process tomatoes briefly in a blender.
Add tomatoes, rice, salt and pepper to onion mixture.
Cover and cook until rice is tender, about 45 minutes, adding water if necessary.
Remove pepper slices before serving.

title: maple syrup marinade
directions: Mix in plastic bag.
Add meats.
Place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Melt oleo and chips either in microwave or on stove.
Add sugar, eggs, pecans and vanilla.
Add flour last and mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: barbara's oyster casserole
directions: Layer, starting with crackers, in casserole.
Add cream and butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Melt butter; mix with sugar and cornmeal.
Add beaten eggs. Add pineapple and coconut.
Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Measure corn syrup and brown sugar into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and raisins.
Add Special K cereal.
Stir until well coated.
With back of spoon, press mixture evenly and firmly into a 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Let stand until cool. Cut into bars.
Yields 20 bars.
Each serving provides:

title: custard
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly until thick.
Add vanilla.
When cool, stir in Cool Whip.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°; grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan with shortening, using pastry brush or paper towel. Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in large bowl with a cooking spoon.
Sift or stir other ingredients together; and stir into banana mixture.
Pour into pan.
(Pan can also be lined with waxed paper.)
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes, until wooden pick inserted in center of bread comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes; then loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove from pan.
Cool before slicing. Kid tested recipe.

title: breaded shrimp
directions: Roll shrimp in flour, then dip shrimp in mixture of egg and milk (1 tablespoon of milk to 1 egg).
Roll shrimp in crushed Club crackers.
Fry in hot oil or shortening until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone it.
Cook the egg noodles and drain. To the egg noodles, add the can of cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup.
Stir together.
Add the chicken.
Stir and warm up on stove over medium heat.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put Veg-All, water chestnuts, 1 cup grated cheese and mayonnaise in large bowl.
Saute chopped onion in 1/4 stick margarine until
onion is clear.
Add to vegetables.

title: chicken dumplings and rice
directions: In an electric skillet or large skillet, simmer butter and onion.
Add soups, broth and chicken.
Cut the biscuits into quarters and place on top of the chicken mixture.
Simmer uncovered for about 10 minutes, then cover and simmer 20 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecue chicken(by edna bell)
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Spread nuts in bottom of pie shell and pour in filling. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake Jiffy corn bread according to directions; cool and crumble.
chop pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Mix well with 1/2 cup pickle juice and cooked, crumbled bacon.
Mix the mayonnaise and 1/3 cup pickle juice.
Layer 1/2 of cornbread, 1/2 tomato and 1/2 of mayonnaise mixture over top.
Repeat; reserve some bacon over the top before serving.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and dry mix.
Break or cut up cauliflower into kind of small pieces.
Slice radishes very thin. Slice cucumbers very thin.
Chop green onions.
Combine mixtures and let set in refrigerator at least 2 hours.

title: avocado-crab salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all but avocados and crabmeat.
Cut avocados in half lengthwise.
Scoop out flesh with a spoon, reserving the shells.
Cut flesh into bite size pieces and add to dressing.
Drain all liquid from crabmeat and cut into bite size pieces.
Add to other ingredients and toss lightly.
Spoon salad into avocado shells and garnish with lemon slice.
This is a great accompaniment to grilled T-bone steak or prime rib!

title: pecan millionaires
directions: Mix whipping cream and half and half and set aside.
Bring other ingredients plus one cup of the cream mixture to a rolling boil and add very slowly so mixture does not stop boiling the rest of the cream mixture.
Boil to soft ball stage (242°).
Remove from heat and add 2 cups chopped pecans and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and cut into small squares. Melt in top of double boiler 12 ounces milk chocolate chips and 1/4 pound paraffin.
Dip into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.
Let set until firm.
Makes approximately 80 to 100 pieces.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or food processor. Blend until potatoes are grated.
Do not overblend.
Pour batter onto a hot, well-greased griddle.
Brown on both sides. These will be thin. Spread with butter and roll up like a tortilla to eat or real good with vegetable soup.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Soak bourbon and nuts overnight.
Melt margarine.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add nuts.
Cream with fork until smooth and can be handled without sticking to fingers and form into balls and allow to harden.
Dip in unsweetened chocolate melted in a double boiler.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise
into 1/4-inch ovals, then slice each oval lengthwise into matchsticks.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add butter, eggs and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Use whites for meringue.
Pour into cooked 9-inch pie crust.
Put meringue on and brown in oven.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine onions, green pepper and celery.
Fry in bacon drippings for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, sugar and tomato paste.
Stir to break tomatoes.
Let this mixture simmer slowly to thick consistency, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper. Fifteen minutes before serving, add cooked shrimp and stir.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings and goes well with a mixed green salad.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix and put into greased casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients well, then chill.
Form into a ball and roll into nuts or parsley.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients (sift).
Add additional flour, if it seems thin. Cover and put in refrigerator and let harden.
Roll up and freeze. Cut and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, spinach, dip mix and milk; mix well.
Chill 3 hours to blend flavors.
Stir before serving. Serve with Melba rounds or other crackers.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Soak bulghur in water for 3 hours (or longer).
Drain bulghur in colander until kernels are dry.
Add vegetables, oil, lemon juice, herbs and soy sauce.
Stir.
Place quartered tomatoes around salad.
Enjoy!

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Serve when hardened.

title: elegant peach delight
directions: Combine cake mix and softened margarine.
Press in lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Arrange peaches on top.
Beat sour cream and egg yolks together.
Pour on top of peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Top with whipped cream; sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: chocolate praline cake
directions: Combine in saucepan until butter melts.
Pour into cake pan. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in 9-inch square pan, ungreased.
Pour 1/4 cup water over apples.
Cream butter, flour and sugar.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Spread creamed mixture over apples and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice and beef
directions: Saute cut up bacon in skillet until done.
Remove from skillet and pour off about 1/2 of fat.
Set bacon aside on paper towels to drain.
Brown onion and green pepper in remaining fat.
Add ground beef and salt and cook until browned.
Bring 2 cups water to boil. Add 2 cups Minute rice.
Stir, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix boiling water and lemon jello until dissolved.
Add 7-Up, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Sprinkle oregano on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: margaret's asparagus casserole
directions: Pour juice off asparagus into pan with flour, oleo, cheese, salt, pepper and enough cracker crumbs to thicken.
Add milk, if needed.
Layer asparagus and sauce in baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter.
Microwave on High until butter melts (about 2 minutes). Stir.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Refrigerate in a 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Cut in squares.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Saute frozen breaded veal steaks in hot olive oil until golden brown.
Place browned steaks in shallow baking dish and cover with tomato sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes until cheese melts and browns.

title: easy garlic rolls
directions: Cut dough into 20 pieces; shape into balls.
Combine remaining ingredients and dip dough balls into butter mixture.
Place in lightly greased 9-inch round cake pan.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 20 rolls.

title: garlic stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Trim off any excess fat from chicken. Blanch the garlic cloves in boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes. (You do not have to peel the cloves.)
Drain cloves, remove skins and slice thinly. Combine the garlic with parsley, salt, pepper and lemon rind.
Place about 1 tablespoon mixture under the skin of each chicken breast.

Heat butter and olive oil in a heavy skillet. Brown the chicken, skin side down first, then turn. Brown about 4 minutes on each side. Lower heat and cover skillet. Simmer about 15 minutes, then remove cover. Saute remaining garlic mixture in a little butter.
Stir in lemon juice and spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with extra parsley.

title: deluxe baked potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together. Put into greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot oil.
Transfer chops to 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Slice onions and separate into rings.
Place on chops.
Mix salt, pepper, chili powder, soup and water together and pour over chops.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Chicken can be seasoned according to taste after washing. Sprinkle rice in pan.
Add dry onion soup mix over rice.
Place chicken parts on rice and onion mix.
Spoon or spread mushroom soup over chicken.
Pour 2 1/2 cups water around edges of pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After one hour, pour remaining 2 1/2 cups of water around edge of pan.
Bake 1 hour more.

title: laura's pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into ungreased 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix over top.
Sprinkle melted butter over cake mix.
Add chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, no longer.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: potatoes with crumbs
directions: Peel potatoes, cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes and cook "al dente. Saute potatoes, bread crumbs, rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper in olive oil until as brown as you like.
Adjust quantities to your needs and taste.

title: homemade soda crackers
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add to flour mixture, stirring well.

title: blind date cake
directions: Combine dates and boiling water and cool.
Add 1 teaspoon soda. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Combine dates with shortening and add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan (9 x 13-inch) and top with one of the following:

title: french onion soup
directions: In Dutch oven, heat margarine and oil over medium heat.
Add onions, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are soft, about 10 minutes. Reduce to low, stirring occasionally, until onions are caramelized.
This should take about 1 hour and 15 minutes. Stir flour into onions.
Bring to a bubble. Cook about 3 minutes.
Slowly stir in beef stock and water. Simmer, partially covered, for 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 325°. Cut French bread into 4 slices.
Bake until dry, about 6 minutes each side.
Heat broiler.
Pour soup into heatproof serving bowl.
Put 1 slice of bread into each bowl and top with cheese.
Broil until golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: eggs "a la goldenrod"(creamed eggs on toast)
directions: Hard-boil eggs.
Cool.
Mix cornstarch and cold water in small bowl.
Heat milk to boiling.
While milk is heating.
Slice egg whites into milk.
Mash egg yolks and set aside.
When milk starts boiling, slowly add cornstarch and water mixture until you get desired thickness to the sauce.
Serve on toast.
Sprinkle with mashed egg yolks.

title: stuffed peaches (salad)(diabetic)
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, pineapple and lemon juice; fill peach halves with cheese mixture.
Serve peaches on a bed of lettuce.
Yields 2 servings.
One serving equals 1 1/4 fruits and 1 lean meat exchange.

title: marinated green bean salad
directions: Mix dry mustard with 1 tablespoon of vinegar until completely dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients except beans and onions; mix well.
Pour over green beans and marinate for at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve cold with finely chopped onions sprinkled over top.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla. Add one egg at a time, beating well after each egg. Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add flour mixture, alternating with sour cream.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: In saucepan, melt butterscotch bits and peanut butter over low heat.
Stir in cereal.
Press 1/2 of mixture into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill.
Set remaining mixture aside.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Cook cocoa, sugar and milk to soft boil.
Add vanilla and butter, if desired.
Take off heat when just starting to thicken and pour into buttered platter.
If too thick, add a little milk and reheat.
Can add 4 tablespoons peanut butter for peanut butter fudge.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; beat eggs and add.
Have milk warm.
Add milk and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell; bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: judy's olive and cheese balls
directions: Mix butter, flour, pepper and cheese into a dough ball.
Pinch off bite size pieces.
Roll in palms.
Mash flat with hands.
Wrap dough around each olive.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 stuffing mix in greased casserole dish.
Place cooked boned chicken over this.
Put 1 can cream of mushroom soup, diluted, with 1/2 can water and 1 can cream of chicken soup, also diluted, over this mixture.
Top with rest of the dressing mix. Dribble chicken broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Mix cloves, cinnamon stick, brown sugar and salt in basket of percolator.
Let perk through full cycle.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 way up sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (or two 9-inch pans).
In same bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed slowly add milk and flavorings.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crust.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all together until smooth.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat all ingredients for 3 minutes and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cracker snack
directions: Drizzle oil over crackers in large 9 x 13 pan. Add 1 package dry Ranch dressing. Add dill weed, teaspoon or more, and garlic salt. Toss. Let dry for few minutes. Put into Ziploc bag.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Heat molasses to boiling.
Pour over butter and sugar.
Add vinegar and mix; cool.
Add egg.
Stir in all dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on floured board, 1 cup at a time.
Keep rest cool.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine slowly.
Mix flour, sugar and salt together. Beat the egg yolks and whole egg together, adding water, lemon juice and margarine.
Mix together well, then add to the sugar-flour mixture.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife in the center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.

title: french cherry dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Add crushed crackers, baking powder, vinegar, vanilla and nuts to egg white mixture.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over cooled egg white mixture. Spread cherry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: zucchini and cheese broil
directions: Place zucchini in casserole.
Put melted butter on top. Sprinkle garlic powder on and top with Feta cheese.
Put under broiler until cheese melts and browns slightly.

title: brunch enchiladas
directions: Combine ham, onions and peppers, plus half of the cheese.
Mix and place 1/8 of mixture at end of each tortilla and roll up. Place seam side down in a greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: casseroll rolls
directions: Scald the milk; stir
in
the
sugar, salt and 1 tablespoon of the margarine and cool to lukewarm.
Melt the rest of the margarine and set aside to cool.
Measure the water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle
in
the yeast and stir until dissolved. Stir in the
lukewarm
milk
mixture
and flour, beating until smooth and elastic
(about 50 strokes).
Brush the top lightly with some of the butter,
cover	and
let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 25 minutes.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix.
Cook with fat meat, after being soaked overnight.
Add 2 quarts water and the next 4 ingredients. Cover, bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, or until beans are done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes more, stirring occasionally.

title: apple pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and egg in 1 1/2-quart bowl on medium speed until smooth. Stir in apple and nuts.
Pour into ungreased pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inches.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve warm.

title: special potato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add next 9 ingredients; cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat and mash vegetables with a potato masher.
Add milk and cheese; cook, stirring constantly until cheese is melted.
Makes 10 cups.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Place chili, half of grated cheese, corn chips, sour cream and corn in a baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with pineapple.
Let cook for 20 minutes; stir constantly and cool.
Mix in buttermilk, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl; chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: super soupy baked potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes about 1 hour before mixing.
Cook at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes in casserole dish.
Serves 8 to 12 usually.

title: homemade graham cracker crust
directions: Heat water to boiling; stir in oil (any brand will do).
Add flour, mixing it with the water and oil.

Place ball of dough into pie plate and, using your fingers, spread the dough over the entire plate, or place between two layers of wax paper and roll or spread to a circle to cover the pie plate.	Bake until light brown.

title: fannie farmer's nut balls
directions: Cream butter, add other ingredients and work with fingers until well blended.
Pinch off bits and roll into balls the size of a large marble.
Bake on lightly buttered cookie sheet at 375° about 10 minutes.
Roll while hot in powdered sugar.
Makes 60.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Marinate at least 1 day.

title: christmas strawberry cake
directions: Soften Jell-O in half cup water.
Combine other ingredients and blend all together in electric mixer for at least four minutes.
Bake in three 9-inch pans, greased and floured, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Cook the milk and flour in a large skillet until thick like gravy.
Add oil, sugar, coconut and pecans.
Stir well into milk mixture and ice cake.

title: athenian chicken
directions: Brown floured chicken in butter (oil).
Set aside while mixing remaining ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil (not potatoes).
Thicken to sauce consistency with 1/2 cup of flour.
Lay chicken in shallow greased pan.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. Fry quartered potatoes in butter until tender.
Place potatoes in same pan as chicken. Serve with fresh green salad.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put eggs, onion, salt, flour, baking powder and 1/2 cup of potato cubes into blender.
Cover and process at #3 until potatoes have gone through the blades.
Stop the blender and add remaining potatoes.
Cover and process at #3 only until all potato cubes have passed through the blades.
Use a rubber spatula to help guide potatoes through processing blades.
Do not overblend.
Pour 1/4 cupfuls onto hot, greased griddle.
Yield: 12 pancakes.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: In a large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 450°.
Stir occasionally.

title: no bake dessert
directions: Crumble cake and spread evenly in an 8 x 12-inch glass pan. Pour pineapple evenly over cake.
Heat marshmallows and milk in a saucepan over low heat until melted; pour evenly over pineapple. Frost cake with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut over top. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: sausage and cheese appetizer
directions: Melt cheese into meat.
Add spices.
Drop by teaspoonful onto bread slices on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: creamy mashed potato bake(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine mashed potatoes, sour cream, milk and garlic powder. Spoon half of mixture into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with 2/3 cup of French fried onions and 1/2 cup cheese. Top with remaining potato mixture. Bake 30 minutes or until hot. Top with remaining 2/3 cup onions and 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Add nuts. Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 1/2 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until creamy color.
Roll in extra sugar.
Cool and roll again.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in large roaster, cover and bake in 250 degrees oven for 5 hours.
