Do not peek. Serves 8 to 10. Leftovers freeze well.

title: shrimp perlow
directions: This is a rice dish unique to the coasts of South Carolina. It's like the Jambalaya of Louisiana; anything can be used to make it.

title: bonnie's vegetable-cheese casserole
directions: Place vegetables in baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and Velveeta.
Pour over vegetables.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and combine with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternating with milk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour.
Add to batter along with coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful into deep fryer. Mixture may be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In medium bowl, combine oil, water, eggs and pumpkin; stir until well mixed.
Combine raisins, walnuts and 2 tablespoons flour in a plastic bag; shake well until coated and set aside.
In separate bowl, combine remaining flour and remainder of ingredients; add liquid ingredients and stir until well coated.
Spoon evenly into prepared pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Recipe will also make 2 dozen muffins. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagne with white sauce(lasagne con salsa balsamella)
directions: Prepare sauces and set
aside.
Cook noodles in boiling water to which you add
olive
oil
to prevent sticking.
When done to "al dente", prepare a
large
baking
pan
and place a layer of sauce, sprinkled
with
a
little Parmesan cheese and pepper. Place a layer of white sauce and repeat process until all ingredients are used, ending
with red sauce.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until top
of lasagne is golden.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift, then measure flour. Sift again with salt and soda added. Cream shortening and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add flavoring. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream. Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake leaves sides of pan.

title: stew
directions: Put all of them in a bowl.
Then put them in the oven for 9 hours.
Get them out of the oven and eat it.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; place in bottom of ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan, pinching edges to seal.
Brush with egg. Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes; cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch mix until well blended.
Spread over crust; sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut in bite size pieces.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in electric blender and blend for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased Pyrex 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Serve chilled. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain well and reserve juice of first 3 fruits listed. Combine fresh fruits to canned fruits and nuts.
Mix juice with pudding mix; combine fruits to this.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water.
Drain.
Combine first 5 ingredients, then add macaroni and chill.

title: betty's apple slices
directions: Crust:	Sift 4	cups
flour with 2 teaspoons salt.
Add Crisco and cut
into
size
of small peas.
Shake lemon juice, egg yolks and
cold
water together.	Add to flour.
Work with dough until it can
be formed and rolled out.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out 1
portion	to
jelly roll pan size.
Pat into pan.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Add sour cream, cocoa and mashed potatoes.
Beat in ginger, vanilla, soda and salt. Blend in nuts, raisins and apples.
Add flour, mixing slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gently fold in.
Bake in tube pan or can bake in coffee cans and cut in half when done to look like logs. Ice with coffee icing.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Add sugar, butter and salt to milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in softened yeast and 1 well beaten egg.
Sift flour and cinnamon together; add to liquid with currants and mix well.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size.
Shape in large biscuits and place on well-greased baking pan.
Let rise.
Use remaining egg, beaten, to brush tops of biscuits.
Cut a cross on each biscuit with sharp knife.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
When cool, add crosses of confectioners frosting.
Makes 3 dozen buns.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello completely with boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Chill until firm.

title: shrimp nibbles
directions: Blend mayonnaise and cheese; set aside.
Arrange Triscuits on baking sheet.
Top with 1 or 2 shrimp and 1 teaspoon cheese mixture.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Filling may be prepared ahead.
Serves 8.

title: betty ann's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix
all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer until thickened
but not thick.
It will get thicker as it is cooked on meats.

title: cracker jack
directions: Melt butter; stir in sugar, Karo and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Put in big roasting pan.
Mix well.
Put in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes and cool, then pack in airtight container.

title: banana jumbos(marry me cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.	Stir in bananas, milk and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, blend flour, soda, nuts and salt.
Stir into batter.
For best results refrigerate batter for an hour before cooking.

title: chili soup
directions: Slice or chop several onions and cook until limp in oil.
Add ground beef and cook until pink has left beef.
Add chili mix.
In your soup kettle put tomato soup and water.
Add the meat mixture to this; bring to boil, then simmer for awhile.
You can adjust this any way you like, using less water, more or less beans, whatever you want.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Boil noodles as directed on package.
Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Mix cottage cheese and sauce with hamburger meat.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put layer of noodles, layer of meat, layer of cheese, and ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown in skillet, hamburger and onion, then drain grease off. Add pork and beans, kidney beans, ketchup, mustard and sugar.
Mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: golden curried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a 9 x 13-inch ovenproof glass baking dish.
Arrange chicken in prepared dish.
Set aside.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump in 13x9 inch pan or dish in above order and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla chip casserole
directions: Layer meat, chips and onion in greased casserole (green onions look pretty).
Mix milk with soup until smooth.
Beat in egg until well blended.
Add rest of ingredients, beating well.
Pour over meat and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: plantation crunch
directions: Melt Candiquick or bark.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour onto large cookie sheet that is lined with waxed paper.
Spread as thin as you can.
Place in refrigerator 5 minutes until set. Break into bite size pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows. Beat until creamy.
Pour over cracker crumbs and coconut.
Stir and drop on wax paper.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Combine beef and pork, then brown. Remove all grease and add spices. While meat is still warm, add Velveeta and mix well. Scoop and spread mixture on party size rye bread. If not serving right away, place on cookie sheets and freeze. When frozen, place in zip lock bags and return to the freezer. When ready to serve, replace on cookie sheet and heat for 15 minutes at 400 (no need to defrost before heating).

title: maymie's pie
directions: Beat the ingredients 10 minutes on high speed in mixer.
Pour into 9-inch glass greased pie pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in preheated 325° oven.
Remove from oven and let stand 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large sauce pot, saute the bell pepper, onion, and minced garlic in the oil until onions are soft but not browned.
Add the ground chuck and cook until meat is no longer pink.
Drain excess grease.
Add the canned tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, Italian seasoning, sugar, and Worcestershire sauce.
Add salt and black pepper, to taste.
Bring mixture to a boil then reduce heat to low.
Simmer the sauce for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed. This sauce is good on spaghetti or in lasagna.

title: french pancakes
directions: Sift flour.
Sift again with salt, baking powder and powdered sugar.
Beat together eggs, milk, water and vanilla or lemon rind. Make a well in the sifted ingredients.
Pour in liquid ingredients. Combine with a few swift strokes.
Ignore the lumps.
Heat a 5-inch skillet.
Grease with a few drops of oil.
Add a small quantity of batter to skillet.
Tip skillet and let batter spread over the bottom.
Cook over moderate heat.
When brown underneath, reverse and brown on other side.
Use a few drops of oil for each pancake. Spread each pancake with jelly or fruit compote.
Roll and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Yields 14 to 16 (5-inch) pancakes.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a double boiler. Combine cake mix with 1/3 cup milk, 3/4 cup butter (melted), 6 ounce chocolate chips and 1 cup nuts.
Mix. Butter 13 x 9-inch pan. Press half of mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle remaining chips over tops.
Pour melted caramels over chips.
Crumble other half of dough over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
(May substitute walnuts for pecans and margarine for butter.)

title: baked water chestnuts
directions: Wrap whole chestnuts in half slices of bacon.
Put in ungreased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered, at 325°.
Remove from oven and drain grease, then mix ketchup, sugar and lemon juice and pour over chestnuts.
Then bake for 20 minutes.

title: noky
directions: Stiff together flour and salt, add water and eggs, beat smoothly and add melted butter.
Drop 1/2 tsp dumpling batter into 3 quarts boiling salted water, let cook.
After they rise to the top let them boil about 5 minutes.
Drain, pour in a glass bowl and add 2 Tbsp melted butter to prevent sticking.

title: green bean salad
directions: Heat until boils the vinegar, sugar, oil and celery seed.
Let cool some, then pour over beans and let stand at least 12 hours.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in bowl the sugar and flour. Put the oleo, cocoa, water, shortening, eggs, soda and vanilla in pan; bring to a boil and then pour over the sugar and flour. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add soup, milk, cheese and rice.
Blend well.
Drain broccoli and mix with other ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni.
Meanwhile, brown hamburger, chopped onion and salt.
Add remaining ingredients. Place half of the mixture into a casserole dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and another layer of cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Slice pepperoni on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut on top.
Bake as directed on cake mix box.
Cook pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes. Pour over cake while still warm.

title: savory pineapple cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese needs to be somewhat softened.
Drain the pineapple thoroughly.
Mix 1/2 cup pecans and the remaining ingredients; chill.
Form into ball or log; roll in remaining pecans.
Chill at least overnight, as the flavors need time to blend.

title: chili verde
directions: In 6-quart saucepan, combine the pork that has been cut up in 1-inch cubes with fat trimmed off, garlic and 1/2 cup stock. Cook, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove lid.
Cook, stirring often, until liquid caramelizes (20 minutes).
Add remaining broth, deglazed.
Add tomatoes with juice, chilies, onions and oregano. Cover and simmer.
Stir occasionally until meat pulls apart easily or 1 1/2 hours.

title: jodi's minnesota fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and top with cut up cherries.

title: red raspberry jelly
directions: Cook raspberries, just use about 1/2 cup water to start off, on low heat;
then increase heat to medium.
Berries will make their own juice.
Put berries in cheesecloth bag to drain juice. Hang to drain juice in a bowl for a few hours.

title: kock kaese
directions: Mix flour, butter and milk in a heavy saucepan or double boiler over low heat, stirring constantly, until you have a thick sauce.
Remove from heat.
Add diced Swiss cheese until cheese melts.
(May add caraway seed.)

title: christmas rocks
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add soda dissolved in coffee. Add cocoa and spices; add the other ingredients dredged in flour. Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: oat bran muffins(healthy)
directions: *You can make your own oat flour by finely grinding oats in the blender.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, sugar and Raisin Bran.
Add eggs, oil and milk. Mix well.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Mixture can be kept in covered container in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: kristen and grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time. Add flour and whipping cream alternately. Add flavoring. Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 325° for an hour and 15 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat the milk until scalding.
Crumble toasted bread into bowl.
Pour milk over this; cool.
Add the melted butter.
Add sugar, eggs and salt.
Pour raisins into mixture.
Add cinnamon. Stir these ingredients together.
Grease bowl with a little butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add broccoli and stir well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes or cheese crackers.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter or lard with sugar.
Mix plain flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa and soda.
Add to sugar mixture, mixing with milk and hot water.
After mixing batter, add vanilla.
Bake in round cake pans and frost with brown sugar frosting or caramel frosting.

title: pineapple salad(great as a side dish or dessert)
directions: Mix over medium heat until thick.
Cool completely.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first nine ingredients well, then add raisins and pecans.
Put in 4 greased and floured coffee cans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain, mash and measure 1 cup.
Combine squash and egg. Stir well.
Mix dry ingredients and onion.
Add squash mixture to dry ingredients and stir until all is well blended.
Drop squash mixture by level tablespoonful into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Drain well.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Quarter squash and onions; cook until tender.
Drain and mash. Add egg, milk, garlic, about 30 crumbled crackers and 1 cup cheese (reserve rest for later).
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with more crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle casserole with remaining cheese before last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water, pour in milk when it cools.
Mix all ingredients together well and chill.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large roaster, combine beef and chopped onion.
Brown, stirring well.
Add taco seasoning, corn, beans, tomatoes, water and broth; stir well.
Bring to boiling point, then turn heat down and simmer for 2 hours.
Or it could be cooked in a crock-pot all day.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Pat into 2 pie tins or jelly roll pan.
Spread it like pie dough with your fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine pineapple and sprinkle powdered pudding on top.
Mix well and cook until it thickens.
Pour into cooled crust and top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water, stirring until jello is dissolved.
Fold in strawberries with juice, nuts and pineapple. Put half of the mixture in mold or pan as first layer. Refrigerate until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Spread top with sour cream. Gently spoon rest of mixture over sour cream. Refrigerate until congealed.

title: oatmeal apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: buffet salad
directions: Put all in a dish and chill until set.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, Crisco and egg yolks.
Add flour, soda, buttermilk, vanilla and chopped walnuts.
Whip egg whites and fold into mixture.
Bake at 325° until just done with toothpick test, 40 or 45 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: grandma's easy overnight french toast
directions: Place bread cubes in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In medium bowl, beat together eggs, milk, brown sugar, vanilla and cinnamon until well blended.
Pour over bread and lightly toss until bread is evenly coated.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until golden brown and set, about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with confectioners sugar or maple syrup.

title: vinegar candy
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Wash down sides of pan with pastry brush dipped in cold water.
Boil mixture to brittle stage (256° on candy thermometer).
Slightly cool, then pull until white and cut into small pieces with scissors or sharp knife.
Arrange pieces on slightly buttered plates to cool.
So good!

title: cherry fluff
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Pour into glass serving bowl. Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crescent caramel swirl
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Coat bottom and sides of 12 cup fluted pan with 3 tablespoons of nuts.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to butter.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove dough from cans in rolled sections; do not unroll.
Cut each section into 4 slices.
Arrange 8 slices in prepared pan, separating each pinwheel slightly to allow sauce to penetrate.
Spoon half of brown sugar mixture over dough.
Repeat with remaining dough and brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes; invert onto serving platter.
Makes 12 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash potatoes.
Pare.
Cut in half or thick slices lengthwise.
Brown well in butter in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle sugar over potatoes.
Add honey, orange peel and orange juice.
Cover dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover. Continue baking 20 to 30 minutes, until potatoes are tender. Baste often with juices in dish or with additional melted butter mixed with brown sugar.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Peel fresh peaches; cut into halves, placing cut side down into unbaked pie shell.
Spread mixture over peaches.
Bake 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, corn, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, egg, onion and 1 tablespoon butter.
Put in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Combine rest of butter and cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix together, then pat in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before adding next layer.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch. Stir with whisk. Stir both milks together and add half to sugar mixture. Microwave 3 minutes. Add 3 egg yolks to the remaining milk and stir until smooth. When first mixture comes out of microwave, stir well. Add the rest of milk to it and stir good. Microwave another 3 minutes. Take out and stir. If it is not thick enough, put back in microwave about 1 minute or if it is too thick, add a small amount of whole milk to it. Add butter and vanilla. Stir until smooth. Pour into pie shell. Let set while you make icing.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: year round broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
For Sauce:
Melt 2 tablespoons butter. Blend in flour, salt and cian pepper.
Gradually add milk; simmer and stir until thick.
Stir in cream cheese until smooth.
In 1/2-quart casserole dish, place broccoli and pearl onions.
Pour in sauce; mix lightly.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes.
Then cut remaining butter in hunks.
Lay on top and sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter on low heat, add cocoa, set aside.
In bowl combine sugar and flour, add cocoa mixture then add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Best if let completely cool before slicing.

title: easy oyster stew
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt margarine and add oysters along with their liquid.
Cook until the oysters begin to curl.
Add remaining ingredients and heat slowly.
Do not boil.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer cabbage in casserole dish.
Cover cabbage good with potatoes.
Add few pepper strips.
Add salt and pepper.
Add onions and few pepper strips.
Add corn and rest of pepper strips.
Top with sausage.
Sausage should cover top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Good with corn bread.

title: sweet salad
directions: Mix ingredients; bring to a boil.
Then pour over medium head of cabbage, chopped.
Cover container,
then set in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Don't stir until ready to serve.

title: italian meatball spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, tomato paste, onion, parsley, garlic, oregano, fennel seed and salt in deep saucepan.
Rinse tomato paste cans with water; add to sauce.
Add meatballs.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until thickened to desired consistency.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti with green salad and garlic bread.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles. Mix liquid ingredients. Add noodles, raisins and almonds. Top with cornflake crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Fold into first ingredients and chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rhubarb dream dessert
directions: Combine butter, powdered sugar and 1 cup flour.
Press into 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: one skillet swiss steak
directions: In pie plate combine flour, seasoned salt and pepper.
Coat steak with flour mixture.
In large skillet, heat oil and brown steak on both sides.
Add tomatoes, onion and garlic powder with parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add corn and green pepper; cover and simmer 15 minutes longer.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/2 batter into a greased 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: yummy munchies
directions: Heat, do not boil, the sugar and syrup.
Add peanut butter and mix in Rice Krispies.
Spread in pan and let cool.

title: nutty no-sugar brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil the bottom only of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: chili vegetable soup
directions: In large pan cook beans and onion in water and bacon grease until soft.
Dice potatoes, carrots and green beans and add to pinto beans.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Add this and remaining ingredients to beans.
Cook slowly about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.

title: justine cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars thoroughly in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift flour with soda and salt; add to mixture. When blended, stir in oatmeal, dates and nuts.

title: granny ruth's potato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop by spoonfuls onto a heated skillet, using cooking oil.
Brown bottom side; flip over with spatula.
Cakes are ready when both sides are brown.

title: egg bake
directions: Cut crust from bread and cut into 1 inch cubes.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard well.
Pour egg mixture over bread crumbs which should be placed in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add crumbled, uncooked sausage.
Place grated cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Great for Sunday breakfast.

title: apple-stuffed acorn squash
directions: Wash squash; cut in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add 1/2 inch boiling water and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pasta and ham salad
directions: Cook rings 6 to 8 minutes; drain. In a large bowl, add all the ingredients; mix well. Serve on lettuce.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in tightly covered jar; shake well. Refrigerate 3 hours.
Shake thoroughly before serving (will keep long time in refrigerator).

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cut slices of bread into doughnuts (with a doughnut cutter) with holes.
Keep leftover bread.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover bottom with pieces of holes of the bread.
Layer with cheese, broccoli and ham.
Top with the doughnut pieces of bread.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour on top.
Sprinkle with paprika on top. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes uncovered.
Let stand 10 minutes and cut into pieces.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Combine soup with 2 cups of water and rice in a baking dish. Place chicken parts on top of mixture; sprinkle onion soup over all.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.
Don't peek.
(Pork chops can be used instead of chicken.)

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and 1/2 cup water, tomato paste, garlic, salt, pepper, chili powder, mustard and chopped onions.
Add 2 cups water and the sugar.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: corn scallop
directions: Drain liquid from whole kernel corn into a cup.
Save 1/4 cup of liquid.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in 1/4 cup of liquid and other ingredients.
Spoon into 8-cup baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
It can be made with Jack cheese or Mozzarella but Swiss is better.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine sugars, soda and flour.
Cut in butter until particles are size of cornmeal.
(Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture for the topping.)
Add vanilla and buttermilk to remaining mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add nuts and chips to reserved mixture and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Brown chicken in oleo.
Remove from skillet to cool.
In the same skillet, add soup, water, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Shred chicken into small pieces and put into soup mixture.
Bring to a boil, stir in Minute Rice.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed.

title: corn muffins
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Mix egg, milk and shortening. Add to dry ingredients.
Mix quickly and pour into 12 greased (or Pammed) 2-inch muffin tins or a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: berry-colada  punch
directions: Process strawberries and cream of coconut in a blender until smooth. Pour into a pitcher or large bowl. Stir in pineapple juice, club soda and, if desired, rum. Serve over crushed ice. Yield: 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Coat chicken in mixture of onion soup mix and bread crumbs. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° on a greased cookie sheet. Check and turn.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, peanut butter, coconut, vanilla and\\ pecans.
Shape into small balls, put toothpicks in each one and chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Dip each ball in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
Remove toothpicks when balls are cooled.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Cook noodles 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Prepare spinach. Drain.
Saute onion in oil.
Add carrots and mushrooms and cook until crisp-tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste and oregano. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, spinach sauce and 1/3 cheese.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
(I use extra carrots and mushrooms and only have 2 layers.)

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add the beaten eggs and flour. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook slow (275° to 300°) for about 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: diabetic - walnut macaroons
directions: Combine oats, sugar replacement, salt, vanilla and liquid shortening in medium mixing bowl; stir to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add beaten egg and chopped walnuts; stir to blend thoroughly.
Pack a small amount of mixture level into teaspoon.
Pat out onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 42 cookies.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add oleo and beat again.
Stir in oats.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust. You may sprinkle chopped nuts over the top, if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes, or until done.
(Center of pie will seem firm.)
Also freezes well.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients except bread.
Remove crust from bread.
Spread mixture on bread and cut each slice into triangle shape pieces (4 pieces, each slice).
Fry in deep hot oil, shrimp side down.
Turn over and fry bread side a few more seconds.
Drain on paper towel.

title: hearty macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and cool thoroughly.
Reserve 1 wedged egg.
Cut remaining eggs in half horizontally.
Combine egg, tuna, celery, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir in macaroni.
Chill thoroughly before serving. Garnish with remaining egg wedges.
Makes 6 to 8 main dish servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers.
Melt marshmallows in milk.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Put all ingredients (I mix with my hands) in buttered tube pan and refrigerate for 4 hours.
Serve after letting sit out for a while.
(Tastes like a candy bar!)

title: walnut chicken
directions: Blend soy sauce into cornstarch.
Stir in sherry, ginger root, sugar, salt and red pepper.
Preheat wok or skillet over high heat.
Stir-fry peppers and onions in oil about 2 minutes. Remove.
Add walnuts to wok and stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Remove. Add half of chicken to wok; stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Remove and stir-fry other half.

title: dump cake
directions: Into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan, spread pie filling evenly. Now layer drained pineapple over pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Spread pecans evenly over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine sugar and flour and spread on shallow plate; dip both sides of each tomato into mixture.
Combine egg and milk; dip each tomato slice into liquid mixture.
Dip each tomato slice into dry bread crumbs.
Fry in the oil until brown on each side.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together until apples are transparent, then add 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Add cinnamon to apples.
Put a topping on of margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and flour, crumbled.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce and Accent until thoroughly blended.
Add 1/2 cup pecans and 1/2 cup parsley. Shape into a ball and chill overnight.

title: rice with lentils
directions: Saute onion in oil until brown.
At the same time, cook lentils in water with salt and garlic.
After browning onion, add to lentils, along with rice, olive oil and allspice.
Cover pan; cook about 15 minutes, or until creamy.

title: daube a la provencale(beef stew provencal)
directions: In a 5 to 6 quart kettle over medium heat, cook bacon for about 5 minutes.
Add beef, about a quarter at a time and cook until browned on all sides.
Stir in carrots, onions, bay leaves, thyme, rosemary, savory and wine.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat, simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours until meat is very tender.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
If mixture seems dry, add some milk to moisten.
Bake at 400° to 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Continue baking 90 minutes.

title: meat squares
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn to 325° for 30 minutes (check).

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Put slices of rye and white bread in a 9-inch Corning Ware skillet.
Pour 1 cup water over bread.
When soaked, crumble into fine pieces with your hands.
Combine with chopped onion, chopped parsley, beef, grated cheese, slightly beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape mixture into a loaf right in Corning Ware skillet.
Dot top with butter and bake, uncovered, in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over loaf.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: andagi
directions: Fold ingredients together.
Don't mix too much, just until a soft consistency.
Use ice cream scoop to place into pan of cooking oil (about 2 to 3 inches).
Yields about 30 doughnuts.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put cubed beef in casserole dish.
It is not necessary to brown beef first.
Mix soup, water, onion soup mix and mushrooms; pour over uncooked beef.
Cover; bake for 3 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.
May be made 1 day ahead and reheated.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and egg in bowl.
Stir in flour.
Press dough in bottom of 1/2-inch up sides of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake until edges are light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg, molasses and water.
Mix well.
Sift
in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by spoonful.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
May sprinkle with sugar before baking if you wish to.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain off pan drippings.
Saute onion and garlic in butter in a medium saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over ribs and bake 45 to 60 minutes or until tender, basting occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Mix well and place in refrigerator to jell.

title: easy delicious old fashioned cole slaw dressing
directions: Whisk together all ingredients.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Pour over your favorite salad mix.

title: rice and veggies
directions: Cook rice.
While cooking rice, prepare vegetables.
A variety of vegetables can be used.
I have listed a few veggies we usually use, but feel free to add your own favorites.
To cook vegetables, stir-fry carrots for 1 minute.
Add cauliflower; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add broccoli, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add cooked rice; mix.
Sprinkle soy sauce to taste.

title: sausage bread
directions: Push sausage out of casing and fry until brown; drain off fat. Add beaten egg (save a little to spread over top of loaf), oregano, basil and cheeses.

title: enchiladas el paso
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, onion and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes. Place heaping tablespoonful each of meat sauce and cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up tightly.
Place, seam side down, in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Can be made ahead of time, covered and refrigerated overnight.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat. Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool. Garnish as desired.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon; stir in oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add carrots, nuts and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into a floured and greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
(May also be made into a layered cake.) Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Spread with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: summer squash
directions: Cook onion and squash in small amount of water until tender. Remove from heat.
Drain well.
Mash with potato masher.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover with 1 cup grated American (or other) cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: vegeburger roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 12 x 22-inch greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator yellow tomato preserves
directions: I use yellow cherry tomatoes for this, because they are less acid than the red ones.
Also, oddly enough, I like the crunch of their seeds in this.
The recipe is for the minimum amount you'd want to make.
I usually double it.

title: granola
directions: Mix well in large bowl (use your hands).
Spread thinly on very lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: strawberry salad supreme
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over lemonade in small saucepan to soften. Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into large bowl; add ginger ale, Cool Whip, maraschino cherry liquid and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Chill until mixture has the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in strawberries, almonds and cherries.
Pour into 5-cup crown mold and refrigerate until firm.
Empty mold contents on serving plate. Garnish as desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: little smokies
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot for 2 hours; makes a great party snack.

title: crunchie potatoes
directions: Warm Cheez Whiz in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together, except 1/2 stick oleo and cornflakes, and place in 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350 degrees.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine oats and peanut butter in large bowl.
In saucepan combine butter, milk, and cocoa.
Bring to a heavy boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Pour mixture over oats and peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Cool completely.

title: pumpkin loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. In a large bowl with fork, mix flour with next 7 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and mix until just blended.
Turn batter into pans.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and let set 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for several hours.
Cut into small slices, as this is very rich.

title: autumn soup
directions: Puree tomatoes in a blender; set aside. In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain. Stir in tomatoes and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Discard bay leaf. Serves 10.

title: cheesy beefy cornbread
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cornmeal in bottom of a well-greased skillet.
Cook over medium heat until cornmeal is lightly browned. Set skillet aside.
Combine cornmeal, salt and soda.
Add milk, corn, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Pour half of batter in skillet. Sprinkle cheese, onion, peppers and ground beef which has already been cooked.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Leave cream cheese at room temperature.
Make sure pineapple is well drained.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in nuts.
Place in refrigerator until time to serve.
Serve on crackers.

title: nachos
directions: On each chip, spread refried beans.
Then place an onion ring, slice of banana pepper and then the cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese is melted.
Delicious hot and good even after they get cold.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges well.
Mix the sour cream, marshmallows and coconut together.
Add the fruit and mix gently. Chill 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Store in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: In a 2-quart microwave bowl place apples, water and juice. Cook on High, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring twice. Add sugar and cinnamon.
Use wooden spoon or blender to break up apples.

title: baked onions
directions: Peel onions. Flatten bottom of onion by slicing the root portion off the bottom of the onion. With a sharp knife, cut a small cone shape out around stem of onion. Place 1 teaspoon bouillon and 1 teaspoon butter in this cone. Wrap each onion in aluminum foil; set in baking pan or cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cream cheese spritz
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Work butter and cream cheese in a bowl until creamy.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Beat thoroughly. Add sifted dry ingredients to butter mixture gradually and mix until smooth.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Put star plate in cookie press and fill press with dough.
Force out 2-inch ribbons in the shape of an "S" onto cold, ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until edges are browned.
Remove from sheets and cool on racks.
Dip ends of cookies in Lemon Glaze and then in chopped nuts.
Place on waxed paper until glaze hardens.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Wash broccoli and cut it into bite-sized pieces.
Discard the tough stems.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Arrange the broccoli pieces in the dish.

title: rump pot roast
directions: Wash roast.
Place in roast pan with cover.
Salt and pepper. In a bowl, combine soups and water.
Mix well with fork.
Pour over roast.
Cut bell pepper in slices and lay on top of roast. Put on cover and bake in oven at 350° for about 3 hours.
One hour before done, take out and add the potatoes and carrots.

title: frozen lime daiquiri
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in plastic tub with lid.
Serve slushy.

title: angela's cold pizza appetizer
directions: Roll the crescent dough on the back of 13 x 9-inch pan and bake according to package instructions.
Cool completely, then spread cream cheese, then the veggie dip on top of it.
Sprinkle ham, carrots, tomatoes, broccoli and olives.
Cut in squares of 3 x 3-inch, then serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail; mix with the pudding mix.
Combine all fruit with the pudding mixture. Refrigerate.
(Can add more pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges if desired.)

title: potato salad
directions: Combine cooked potatoes, onion, celery and salt with 1/4 cup French dressing; let stand several hours in the refrigerator.
Add hard-cooked egg and mayonnaise; mix carefully just before serving. Serves 4.

title: 1,000 island dressing
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: hot peppers
directions: Cut peppers.
Cover with vinegar.
Add oregano and garlic. Let soak overnight.
Drain.
Put in jars.
Cover with oil and put lids on.
You do not heat.

title: hermits
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with molasses and sour milk to creamed mixture. Finally, add egg, then raisins.
Spread to thickness of 1-inch on a greased cookie sheet (with sides).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with sugar.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with salt, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Set aside.
Beat eggs well, add vanilla to eggs.
Pour eggs in flour mixture, add oil and work with hands.
Add apples and pecans.
Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Lower heat to 275° and bake 1 hour.

title: mock indian pudding
directions: Pour hot water over the Shredded Wheat biscuits. Drain quickly and mash. Add eggs, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well until biscuits have no lumps.
Add milk and molasses.
Place in lightly buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serve hot or cold with vanilla ice cream.

title: two crust pastry
directions: Take 1/3 cup flour from the 2 cups and put in a cup.
Add cold water.
Stir to a paste and set aside.
Mix the Crisco in the remaining flour until crumbly.
Add the water-flour paste and make into a ball.
Roll half on a sheet of wax paper and flip into pie pan.
Roll the other 1/2 for top crust, or if not using a top crust, put in plastic bag and freeze.
If you want a cooked crust to fill, prick with a fork so you don't get bubbles.
Can fill with fruit pie filling.

title: vegetable salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine the vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and oil.
Bring to a boil; cool completely.
Pour over vegetables. Toss until vegetables are coated.
Cool several hours or overnight.

title: baked chicken l' orange
directions: Place chicken in a baking pan.
Combine soda and soy sauce; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting often. If necessary, make additional soda and soy sauce for basting.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings; add ground beef and brown slightly.
Add all other ingredients except spaghetti.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: pumpkin pie delight(healthy recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray 9 inch pie pan with vegetable pan spray. Place all ingredients in mixing bowl. Beat two minutes with mixer. Pour into pie pan and bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up. Serves 8.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients, except liquid smoke.
Mix by hand.
Then pour liquid smoke over top and continue mixing.
Place in tight, large container in refrigerator.
Each day for 4 days, mix by hand.
Return to refrigerator.
On the 5th day, shape into 3 rolls about 9 inches long and as big around as bottom of a Coke bottle. Place on broiler rack so juice can drip down into pan.
Bake at 140° for 4 hours.
Then turn all rolls over and bake 4 more hours.
Serve cold.
This is not good hot or warm.
Freezes well.

title: white bread
directions: Soak yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Put sugar and salt in pan, then add warm milk and soft shortening. Then add yeast and stir.
Add 6 cups flour and mix well, then add remaining flour.
Knead 6 or 7 minutes by hand.
Let rise.
Work down.
Let rise again.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Take a leaf of lettuce and place on plate. On top of the lettuce, place a slice of pineapple and a pear half. In the center of the pear, put a small dollop of mayonnaise. Sprinkle cheese over all. Place cherry on top. This can be served on plate along with main course, or separate on a salad plate.

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: Saute beef in butter in a large skillet 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups milk, simmering 2 minutes and stirring often. Combine flour and bouillon granules in a small bowl.
Gradually stir in remaining milk.
Gradually stir flour mixture into beef mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Serve over toast or in commercial frozen puff pastry shells (baked).

title: plaza steak soup
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Make a paste of oleo mixed with flour. To water add celery, onions, carrots, Accent, salt, pepper and bouillon cubes.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Then add frozen mixed vegetables and tomatoes.
Mix paste with browned beef and add.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally as it may stick.

title: east-west stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Break ground beef into large chunks and stir-fry 3 minutes or until no longer pink.
Remove meat and set aside.
Add broth, carrots and mushrooms to skillet. Cook over high heat for 3 minutes. Stir in onion, meat and mixture of Worcestershire sauce and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil; cook 1 minute.
Stir in spinach and cook until wilted.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: stuffed baked salmon
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add all other ingredients together and add to onion mixture.
Fill cavity of fish loosely.
If stuffing is dry, add a little milk.
Remove head, tail and fins from fish.
Sprinkle cavity lightly with Accent.
Then stuff with stuffing.
Place on foil in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven, allowing 12 to 15 minutes per pound.
Baste with butter several times as it bakes.
Serve with lemon.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch, sugar, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla and stir until mixed good.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The middle will fall.

title: sugar-free spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.

title: modern meat loaf(serves 8)
directions: Combine ground turkey, ground veal, soup mix, eggs, bread crumbs and seasonings in bowl; mix well.
Pack into large loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done to taste.

title: chocolate eclair cake and frosting
directions: Line cake pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk. Add Cool Whip.
Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers and then pudding mixture.
End layers with graham crackers.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: You will need approximately 24 aluminum cups for this recipe.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: In saucepan over low heat stir water, sugar, and gelatin until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Mix in large mixing bowl and blend for 2 min. milk, vanilla pudding.
Add sour cream and fold in 3 cups whipped topping.

title: ray gardner's cheese toast
directions: Turn oven on broil.
Place bread on ungreased pan.
Butter each slice as desired.
Place cheese on bread.
(For that extra cheesy toast, you can place 2 slices on 1 piece of bread.)
Place pan in oven and cook until desired texture.
Take out of oven and enjoy.

title: st. george's punch
directions: Refrigerate ginger ale and juices overnight. Mix and serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients, except cornmeal mix. Mix well, then add cornmeal mix.
Stir good and pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: yellow tail snapper - hawaiian style
directions: Marinade filets longer than 1 hour if possible. Bake or grill this dish. Top the snapper with pineapple, then bananas. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes; fish should flake with a fork. Grill 10 to 15 minutes each side. Turn once. Do not overcook the bananas.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Brown crumbled meat; drain grease.
Add onion, tomatoes with liquid, mushrooms with liquid and macaroni.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes, stirring often, until macaroni is done and most of liquid is absorbed.
If needed, water may be added to keep mixture moist.
Stir in chili powder, garlic powder and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover only long enough to melt cheese.
Serve in skillet.
Crusty bread and green salad complete this quick meal.

title: california gold rush baking beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion until soft.
Add beans, brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Stir well.
Put in a large baking dish or Dutch oven.
Cover with Parmesan cheese (small amount).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Put eggs in bowl, beat until light.
Add flour, sugar, salt and soda, all sifted together.
Add fruit cocktail, spread 1/4 cup brown sugar and a few crushed pecans on top of batter.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not grease pan.

title: cornell barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in large saucepan.
Heat; do not boil. Dip chicken halves in sauce.
Grill.
Brush on additional sauce as needed.

title: barbecue franks
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and add wieners. Put on high for 30 minutes or until hot. Put on low for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Stir 3 or 4 times.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except peas.
Add salt to taste and add 1/2 cup Miracle Whip.
Add peas before serving.
Delicious on head of lettuce.

title: barbecued wimpies
directions: Brown ground beef in fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini-tomato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and grated cheese (Romano or Parmesan).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: steamed crabs
directions: Cover tightly and cook 30 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In large bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Using fork or pastry blender cut shortening into flour mixture until consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk, stir with fork until mixture leaves side of bowl and forms a soft, moist dough. On floured surface toss lightly until no longer sticky.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick, cut with 2-inch floured cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 450 ° for 8 to 12 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: luncheon pan rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add egg, yeast and flour.
Knead and let rise (about 2 hours).
Knead and shape into rolls, greasing between rolls in a buttered pan.
Let rise until double in size, then bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Makes 20 large rolls.

title: "tater tot" casserole
directions: Let
Tater
Tots
thaw, then chop.
Mix all ingredients except Parmesan
cheese.	Pour into greased 3-quart casserole dish
(or separate
and freeze before cooking).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pineapple banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour bread pans. Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl, mix well.
Pour wet mixture into dry mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into bread pans.
Bake for 1- 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool pans for 10 minutes then remove loafs and let cool on wire rack.
Yield 2 loaves.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish and bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Take out and pour tomato ketchup on top and spread over top.
Put back in oven for 30 minutes.

title: country cassoulet
directions: Cook and stir sausage, celery, onion, green pepper, garlic and salt until the meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in pork and beans (with sauce), lime beans (with liquid) and tomato paste. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: fingerpaint
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch together in a medium saucepan. Add water and continue mixing.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly (be sure to let your mom or dad do this).
Mixture will boil and thicken.
Remove from stove, cool and pour into cups. Add a little food coloring and a drop of detergent.
Now paint!

title: cherry fruit tapioca
directions: Bring juice, salt, sugar and lemon juice to a boil.
Gradually add tapioca.
Cook 15 minutes on low heat, stirring continually. Remove from heat.
Cool.
Fold in cherries and almond extract. Chill.
Serve topped with whipped topping.

title: dill macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and cool.
Add celery, green pepper and carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spoon over macaroni and toss to mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bacony chestnuts
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: caesars salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients.
Pour over lettuce and top with croutons and cheese.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixer bowl beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; set aside.
In bowl combine sugar, flour and salt.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in milk and ReaLemon. Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Fold in egg whites, pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Place in larger pan; fill with 1 inch hot water.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until brown on top.
Cool before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar. Set aside. Cream together oil, Crisco stick and sugars. Mix in vanilla and eggs. Add sifted ingredients. Form into walnut sized balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with glass with bottom dipped in sugar. Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 325° oven. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: oven baked beans
directions: Pour both cans into a casserole dish.
Put barbecue sauce and mustard in the beans.
Chop onion in small pieces and sliced bacon on top.
Cook about 1 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Cut chicken into cubes.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes in microwave.
Combine chicken, broccoli, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Add 1/2 soup mixture.

title: caesar salad
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Clean romaine; place paper towel in between pieces to absorb moisture.
Add croutons.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix dates, whole cherries and pineapple slices in large bowl. Combine flour, baking powder and salt and sift over fruits.
Toss to coat.

title: chicken casserole dinner
directions: Blend dry soup into sour cream and let stand 2 hours.
Place chicken in roasting pan, pour sherry and water over it.
Sprinkle with seasonings and parsley, cover roaster tightly.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, or until meat falls off the bones.
Remove from pan to cool.
Strain juices from pan into a saucepan and simmer until reduced to 1 1/2 cups.
Blend in mushroom soup until smooth and heat a few minutes.
Slowly combine with canned soup and sour cream mixture.
The cream will not curdle if you blend slowly, pouring hot liquid into cream mixture a little at a time.
Cook rice according to directions.
Skin and bone cooled chicken, cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine with rice and turn into buttered casserole.
Pour sauce over and toss lightly.
Heat, uncovered, before serving, at 250° for 30 minutes.
Freezes beautifully. Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine margarine and rice in large baking dish.
Stir in soups.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Blend flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cream cheese is melted (low heat).
Serve over hot noodles.
Garnish with parsley, if desired. Makes 2 servings.

title: christopher masello's incredibly awesome white chocolate-oatmeal
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and water.
In a separate bowl mix together all dry ingredients and stir until spices and soda have been thoroughly blended with flour and oatmeal.
Add dry ingredients to butter/sugar and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on box.
Cook in sheet cake pan or rectangular pan, go by directions on box for this also.
You can leave cake in pan but it is best to put it out of pan.
(I have a sheet cake Tupperware container and I put it out on that.)
Poke holes, rather large, all over cake.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over cake, gradually, using knife to spread over.
Let soak in, then pour the well mixed can of cream of coconut and use the same procedure.
Let set overnight or as long as you want to.
Put in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, ice with whipped topping and add grated coconut on top.
I have kept in refrigerator several days.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch deep pie or quiche plate.
If vegetables are frozen, do not cook.
If vegetables are fresh, cook 5 minutes. Mix all vegetables, cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 1925 great grandma oven barbecue
directions: In covered roasting pan, place meat.
Add onions, chopped. Bake for 1 hour.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Tie pickling spice into a square cheesecloth material.
Tie and make a small ball.
Pour all over meat, add water (cover).
Bake 4 hours until cooked meat falls apart in 350° oven (if dry, add more water).
Thicken with flour and water mixed into a paste.
Remove small pickling bag. Shred meat.
Serve on hamburger buns with sweet relish.

title: sue's lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl mix well cottage cheese, Ricotta cheese, and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese until combined.
In prepare pan spread 1/4 spaghetti sauce.
Place layer of 1/3 noodles, spread with 1/2 cheese mixture, 1/3 Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 spaghetti sauce.
Repeat.
Top with remaining noodles, spaghetti sauce, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: vinegar and oil salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a small jar with a tight lid.
Shake until well mixed.
Makes about 1/3 cup of salad dressing.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour bottom only of a 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.

title: jacquies spanish rice
directions: Put oil in pan to cover bottom.
Add rice.
Saute carefully until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Boil with lid on, then simmer 18 minutes.
Stir again.
Cook until done.

title: raw vegetable pizza
directions: Roll and pinch together the rolls to cover cookie sheet.
May use a 9 x 13-inch pan, but only use 1 package of rolls.
Bake, following directions on package, and cool.
If making
a 9 x 13-inch pan, also cut down on the seasoning.
Combine
the salad dressing, cream cheese and seasoning.
Spread over the baked and cooled crust.
Top with diced vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, fresh mushrooms, carrots, green pepper, bacon bits and any other vegetables you like).

title: monkey shake
directions: Pour milk into blender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend on high for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: grandma's noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add garlic, salt and pepper and sauce. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Grease casserole.
Mix onion with sour cream and cream cheese.
Place 1/3 of noodles in casserole.
Spread with 1/3 of sour cream mixture, then 1/3 of sauce, then grated cheese.
Repeat layers twice and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hurry-up potatoes
directions: Wash and pare 2 medium potatoes.
Cut crosswise in 1/8-inch slices.
Brush broiler rack with a little melted shortening and arrange potatoes on rack.
Brush tops with more melted shortening. Sprinkle with 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Broil until tender, 6 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into bite-size pieces.
Marinate in lots of apple cider.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Spice to taste. Cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks or until tender.
Should serve about 3,799 people.
If more are expected, add the 2 rabbits (but only if necessary; most people do not like "hare" in their stew).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
If mixture is not smooth, add 1 teaspoon of milk at a time until smooth.
(Optional: One to two teaspoons of peanut butter can be added.)
Roll out and cut or drop by spoon.
Sprinkle with plain or colored sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or less.

title: company bean salad
directions: Dilute soup with 1/2 can milk.
Stir until smooth.
Layer ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole 1 can beans, 1/3 of mushroom soup, 1/3 of bacon, 1/3 of Durkee onions and 1/3 of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat until all gone.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: homemade pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate Velveeta cheese and mix all ingredients well.
DO NOT GET TOO SOUPY!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil together one minute.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and graham crackers.
Drop by teaspoon.

title: poor man's pudding(what family didn't qualify in earliest pioneer days?)
directions: Our large family had many special desserts.
We begged for this, always served in a large pale-green bowl.

title: stuffed giant shells
directions: In a skillet, brown chuck, onion and garlic until chuck is crumbly.
Drain excess fat; cool.
Stir in cheese, crumbs, parsley and egg.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook shells in boiling, salted water until almost tender, about 15 minutes. Drain.
Use meat mixture to stuff shells.
Spoon 1/4 of sauce over the bottom of a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place shells on top of sauce side by side in a single layer.
Mix wine with remaining sauce and pour over shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in preheated oven (400°) for 20 to 25 minutes until brown and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Saute chicken in margarine until slightly browned.
Put in a baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer until bubbly.
Spoon over chicken and bake in oven at 325°.
Spoon sauce from bottom of dish over chicken 2 or 3 times.
Good for a picnic, or bake ahead meals!

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add chicken and marinate for 2 hours (at least) or all day.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Broil for a few minutes for crispy skin.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange; add sugar and let stand 1 hour. Mix Jell-O; let begin to thicken.
Stir in other ingredients; let set until jelled.

title: cheese and chutney pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, Cheddar, curry powder and sherry.
Spread in 9-inch glass pie pan.
Spread with chutney.
Cover with almonds and green onions.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix well with sausage.
Add Bisquick and mix well with hands.
Shape into balls 1/2-inch diameter.
Place on cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: southern fried pies
directions: Cook dried fruit.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Crumble shortening into mixture.
Add milk gradually, making a dry dough. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into rounds the size of a saucer. Place tablespoon of cooked fruit on half of round.
Fold over other half.
Moisten edges with cold water and press edges together. Prick top; brown in shallow hot oil.
Turn and brown other side. Drain on paper towel.

title: helen's chicken gumbo
directions: Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces.
Saute chicken in large heavy skillet in butter until well browned on all sides.
Remove chicken to 3-quart saucepan and set aside.
Stir flour into drippings until smooth.
Heat to simmering, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat and stir until flour turns medium brown, about 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth until blended.
Heat to boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour over chicken in saucepan.
Saute onion, green pepper, thyme, hot pepper sauce and bay leaf in oil until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir into chicken.
Cut tomatoes in half.
Stir into chicken along with juice.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer.

title: cool and easy cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions (use a 9 x 13-inch pan).
Cool.
Slice bananas and place on top of cake.
Cover with crushed drained pineapple.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: easy light bread
directions: In mixer bowl, mix first 4 ingredients; cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar. Combine mixtures; add egg and 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Stir in remaining flour until combined.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down; shape dough into loaf. Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let rise in warm place, about 1 hour.
Bake in preheated 425° gas oven 25 to 30 minutes. If top of loaf browns too fast, cover loosely with foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: chocolate rocks
directions: Cover 2 baking sheets with waxed paper and set aside.
Melt chocolate and peanut butter in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir in peanuts and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto prepared baking sheets.
Chill until firm.
Cover tightly and store in cool place.
In hot weather, refrigerate.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until soft.
Add chicken soup, celery soup, olives, salt, pepper and chicken.
Put spaghetti in large amount of salted boiling water.
Let return to rolling boil.
Cover and remove from stove; let stand for 20 minutes without opening.
Drain spaghetti; add chicken mixture, mixing well.

title: 2 pecan pies
directions: Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° until set.

title: easy cake
directions: Do not mix.
Use an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer each ingredients in order and finish by pouring the melted margarine over all.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Make squares and serve with Cool Whip on top of each square.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, molasses and egg.
Mix drying ingredients into creamed mixture.
Chill.
Make into balls and roll in butter and then in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° until golden brown.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix the fruits.
Stir in salad dressing or serve on top of fruits, if desired.
Makes 8 servings, about 4 cups.

title: libby's squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandmaw's homemade rolls
directions: Cream
margarine
with sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add egg and mix together.
In lukewarm water dissolve yeast with 1 teaspoon
sugar.
Sift
salt
with flour.
Add flour and yeast mixture all together with an additional cup of lukewarm water. Add more
sifted flour to make a soft dough.
Toss on a light floured board
and
knead briefly.
Place in covered bowl and allow to double in size in
a warm place.
Knead down and make into rolls or store in refrigerator until about 2 hours before rolls are to be	baked.	Make
out
rolls and place in greased pan.
Allow to rise double size.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Sprinkle a small amount of cornmeal in bottom of pan and brown.
Mix cornmeal, eggs, milk, corn and drippings together; pour half in pan.
Sprinkle cheese over this.
Add meat, onion and peppers.
Pour on rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: 2 easy chicken recipes
directions: Mix together.
Place chicken breasts in pan; season. Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Great over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cold water; dissolve in hot juice. Combine all ingredients together, then freeze.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: new zealand cornflake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add egg and cream again.
Add flour, baking powder and mixed fruit.
Mix well.
Roll teaspoonfuls in lightly crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tortillas
directions: Beat together oil and milk.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of a large walnut.
Set under a bowl or dish for 20 minutes.
Roll out and fry on griddle or electric skillet; watch very closely.

title: corn fritter appetizers
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and pepper together.
Combine egg, milk, corn and bacon; add to flour mixture and mix only until well moistened.
Heat oil 1 1/2-inches deep to 365° in skillet. Drop batter by scant teaspoonful into oil.
Fry until golden, turning once.
Drain; serve once.
Yields about 50 small fritters.

title: stuff in the bucket
directions: Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar until well blended. Add the fruit.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Add the nuts and fold in gently.
Place mixture in a decorative bowl and refrigerate to thoroughly chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove and serve.
A delectable treat for parties!

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring Jell-O and pineapple to a boil.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix jello in large bowl according to package directions and set aside.
Place oranges, apples and cranberries in food chopper. Add jello, along with sugar, crushed pineapple and marshmallows. After jello begins to set, put marshmallows down and mix.
Leave in bowl or put in jars; store in refrigerator.

title: carrot soup
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt butter over moderate heat.
Stir in onion and cook five minutes until soft, but not brown.
Add carrots, stock, tomato paste and rice.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Puree the soup through a food mill or blender until smooth.
Season and stir in cream.
Reheat before serving.
Add butter and garnish with carrot curls.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Prepare Bundt pan;
melt margarine and cover inside of pan. Sprinkle sugar onto margarine.
Mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Take out; let set 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; line bottom with waxed paper.
In medium bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate pieces, pecans, dates and cherries until all are well coated with flour.
In a large bowl, mix at medium speed 3 eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Fold in flour mixture.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Remove from pan and wrap in foil.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat 1/4 cup margarine and 1/4 cup shortening in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 425° until melted.
Coat chicken.
Place skin side down in pan.
Time 30 minutes.
Turn, then cook 30 minutes more.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 450° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Melt the Cheez Whiz and butter.
Hollow out the potatoes while still hot and mash insides.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Alternate cheese sauce and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly and stuff into potato skins. Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: kiwi cream pie
directions: Prepare the pudding, using the milk and sour cream.
Pour the pudding into the pie shell.
Refrigerate the pie until you are ready to serve it.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Combine and bring to boil sugar, cornstarch, water and cinnamon.
Put rhubarb in baking dish and pour sugar mixture over it.
Sprinkle cake mix over top and dot with margarine.
Sprinkle coconut over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: berry mallow yam bake
directions: Combine the flour, brown sugar, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Drain the yams. Toss 1 cup crumb mixture with the yams.
Add raw cranberries.

title: raisin bran bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients; mix dry ingredients.
Combine them, stirring until just mixed in.
Pour batter into oiled pans.
Bake right away at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mocha fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat 1/4 cup nonfat milk.
Stir in coffee powder to dissolve it.
Add rest of nonfat milk, melted butter or oil and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Mix in oats.
Do not overmix.
Combine rest of sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and cocoa with boiling water.
Mix to dissolve cocoa.
Stir in liquor.
Pour in bottom of 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon on batter by large spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: freezer spaghetti sauce
directions: In large saucepan, heat olive oil until hot.
Add garlic and onion and cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer gently, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until thickness desired.
Cool and package in meal size portions.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: peach delight
directions: Combine ingredients. Cover pan and chill.

title: pasta bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place a large frying pan on medium heat and add oil.
When oil is hot add onion; stir a minute, add celery and stir a minute more.
Reduce heat to low, add salt and herbs and cook about 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in grated cheese.
Mix pasta and beans together with the vegetable-cheese mixture and place in a lightly oiled casserole.
Add 1/2 cup water to keep from burning.
Bake, covered, for about 30 minutes, removing cover during last 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all other ingredients with meat and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over pasta.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Let shrimp stand in cold water for 1/2 hour, then drain and separate with fork.
Mix shrimp, cheese mixture and onion. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill and garnish with cherries or any favorites.
Quick and easy.

title: old fashioned chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa well.
Add 3 cups of milk and heat.
In a bowl, mix egg yolks, flour, salt and 3/4 cup milk.
Beat egg mixture until smooth and add to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell (makes two 10-inch or three 8-inch pies). Beat egg whites with 8 tablespoons of sugar and spread on top of pies.
Then brown.

title: thrasher shark in the microwave(super healthy version!)
